pokemon.name: Bulbasaur
pokemon.pokedex: From birth,a sticky paste that it produces forms peculiar patterns on its body. Every Bulbasaur has a slightly different formation.

pokemon.name: Ivysaur
pokemon.pokedex: It burrows itself in sand,then waits for a prey to get closer,which is then showered by a substance similar to glue,blocking its escape.

pokemon.name: Venusaur
pokemon.pokedex: The clay-like substance it secretes is used as a super glue to patch up its den. It carries other Bulbasaur and Ivysaur in its vase.

pokemon.name: Charmander
pokemon.pokedex: The shiny gem on its chest is the very lifeforce of the Pokemon. In the past,poaching severely reduced this Pokemon's population.

pokemon.name: Charmeleon
pokemon.pokedex: Very impatient for its evolution,it feeds on the purest gems in the caves it lives in. While docile,it is quick to anger.

pokemon.name: Charizard
pokemon.pokedex: Usually docile,it becomes incredibly aggressive during mating season. The hand-like appendages on its back allow it to excavate dens inside sturdy gems.

pokemon.name: Squirtle
pokemon.pokedex: While underdeveloped,its tail has enough power to smash aside large boulders.

pokemon.name: Wartortle
pokemon.pokedex: It takes great care of its golden horns,symbol of its pride. If one dares to chip it,it'll throw its foe with a harsh swing of its tail.

pokemon.name: Blastoise
pokemon.pokedex: It uses its tail as a swinging mace,blowing away anything that comes close to it. Most do not survive this encounter unscathed.

pokemon.name: Caterpie
pokemon.pokedex: For protection,it releases a horrible stench from the antenna on its head to drive away enemies.

pokemon.name: Metapod
pokemon.pokedex: It is waiting for the moment to evolve. At this stage,it can only harden,so it remains motionless to avoid attack.

pokemon.name: Butterfree
pokemon.pokedex: It uses its wings to stun it's prey for an easy catch.

pokemon.name: Weedle
pokemon.pokedex: Its poison stinger is very powerful. Its bright-colored body is intended to warn off its enemies.

pokemon.name: Kakuna
pokemon.pokedex: While awaiting evolution,it hides from predators under leaves and in nooks of branches.

pokemon.name: Beedrill
pokemon.pokedex: May appear in a swarm. Flies at violent speeds,all the while stabbing with the toxic stinger on its rear.

pokemon.name: Pidgey
pokemon.pokedex: It is docile and prefers to avoid conflict. If disturbed,however,it can ferociously strike back.

pokemon.name: Pidgeotto
pokemon.pokedex: Very protective of its sprawling territorial area,this PokÃ©mon will fiercely peck at any intruder.

pokemon.name: Pidgeot
pokemon.pokedex: Revered as the "Wings of the Forest",they protect their territories fiercely and will rain down a maelstrom of petals upon offenders who trespass upon their canopies.

pokemon.name: Rattata
pokemon.pokedex: Although the rock formation on its tail makes it less nimble than its Kantonian brethren,it makes Ayreian Rattata a far more formidable opponent. They brutally swing their tails with in battle,oftentimes injuring themselves.

pokemon.name: Raticate
pokemon.pokedex: It's horn and teeth are extremely tough,able to take on even the harshest conditions without suffering even so much as a scratch. However,if either of the two were to ever shatter,this Pokemon will be shunned by its peers and treated as an outcast.

pokemon.name: Spearow
pokemon.pokedex: Populates more in grassy area than cold ones for unknown reasons. It leaves shards of ice wherever it sleeps.

pokemon.name: Fearow
pokemon.pokedex: A curious organ inside its abdomen allows it to mantain very cold temperatures no matter where it lives. When its life would be in peril,it incases itself in ice.

pokemon.name: Ekans
pokemon.pokedex: Moving silently and stealthily,it eats the eggs of birds,such as Pidgey and Spearow,whole.

pokemon.name: Arbok
pokemon.pokedex: To intimidate foes,it spreads its chest wide and makes eerie sounds by expelling air from its mouth.

pokemon.name: Pikachu
pokemon.pokedex: When Pikachu meet,they'll touch their tails together and exchange electricity through them as a form of greeting.

pokemon.name: Raichu
pokemon.pokedex: If its electric pouches run empty,it raises its tail to gather electricity from the atmosphere.

pokemon.name: Sandshrew
pokemon.pokedex: It burrows into the ground to create its nest. If hard stones impede its tunneling,it uses its sharp claws to shatter them and then carries on digging.

pokemon.name: Sandslash
pokemon.pokedex: It climbs trees by hooking on with its sharp claws. Sandslash shares the berries it gathers,dropping them down to Sandshrew waiting below the tree.

pokemon.name: Nidoran♀
pokemon.pokedex: It uses its hard incisor teeth to crush and eat berries. The tip of a female Nidoran's horn is a bit more rounded than the tip of a male's horn.

pokemon.name: Nidorina
pokemon.pokedex: If the group is threatened,these Pokémon will band together to assault enemies with a chorus of ultrasonic waves.

pokemon.name: Nidoqueen
pokemon.pokedex: It pacifies offspring by placing them in the gaps between the spines on its back. The spines will never secrete poison while young are present.

pokemon.name: Nidoran♂
pokemon.pokedex: The horn on a male Nidoran's forehead contains a powerful poison. This is a very cautious Pokémon,always straining its large ears.

pokemon.name: Nidorino
pokemon.pokedex: It's nervous and quick to act aggressively. The potency of its poison increases along with the level of adrenaline present in its body.

pokemon.name: Nidoking
pokemon.pokedex: One swing of its mighty tail can snap a telephone pole as if it were a matchstick.

pokemon.name: Clefairy
pokemon.pokedex: It is said that happiness will come to those who see a gathering of Clefairy dancing under a full moon.

pokemon.name: Clefable
pokemon.pokedex: Their ears are sensitive enough to hear a pin drop from over a mile away,so they're usually found in quiet places.

pokemon.name: Vulpix
pokemon.pokedex: While young,it has six gorgeous tails. When it grows,several new tails are sprouted.

pokemon.name: Ninetales
pokemon.pokedex: Very smart and very vengeful. Grabbing one of its many tails could result in a 1,000-year curse.

pokemon.name: Jigglypuff
pokemon.pokedex: Jigglypuff has top-notch lung capacity,even by comparison to other Pokémon. It won't stop singing its lullabies until its foes fall asleep.

pokemon.name: Wigglytuff
pokemon.pokedex: It's proud of its fur,which is fine and delicate. In particular,the curl on its forehead has a texture that's perfectly heavenly.

pokemon.name: Zubat
pokemon.pokedex: It emits ultrasonic waves from its mouth to check its surroundings. Even in tight caves,Zubat flies around with skill.

pokemon.name: Golbat
pokemon.pokedex: Its feet are tiny,but this Pokémon walks skillfully. It sneaks up on sleeping prey before sinking in its fangs and slurping up blood.

pokemon.name: Oddish
pokemon.pokedex: During the day,it stays in the cold underground to avoid the sun. It grows by bathing in moonlight.

pokemon.name: Gloom
pokemon.pokedex: Its pistils exude an incredibly foul odor. The horrid stench can cause fainting at a distance of 1.25 miles.

pokemon.name: Vileplume
pokemon.pokedex: It has the world's largest petals. With every step,the petals shake out heavy clouds of toxic pollen.

pokemon.name: Paras
pokemon.pokedex: Burrows under the ground to gnaw on tree roots. The mushrooms on its back absorb most of the nutrition.

pokemon.name: Parasect
pokemon.pokedex: The larger the mushroom on its back grows,the stronger the mushroom spores it scatters.

pokemon.name: Venonat
pokemon.pokedex: Lives in the shadows of tall trees where it eats bugs. It is attracted by light at night.

pokemon.name: Venomoth
pokemon.pokedex: The wings are covered with dustlike scales. Every time it flaps its wings,it looses highly toxic dust.

pokemon.name: Diglett
pokemon.pokedex: It sits in one location,only bothering those who try to pass directly through it.

pokemon.name: Dugtrio
pokemon.pokedex: It sits in one location,only bothering those who try to pass directly through it.

pokemon.name: Meowth
pokemon.pokedex: It washes its face regularly to keep the coin on its forehead spotless. It doesn't get along with Galarian Meowth.

pokemon.name: Persian
pokemon.pokedex: Its elegant and refined behavior clashes with that of the barbaric Perrserker. The relationship between the two is one of mutual disdain.

pokemon.name: Psyduck
pokemon.pokedex: As Psyduck gets stressed out,its headache gets progressively worse. It uses intense psychic energy to overwhelm those around it.

pokemon.name: Golduck
pokemon.pokedex: This Pokémon lives in gently flowing rivers. It paddles through the water with its long limbs,putting its graceful swimming skills on display.

pokemon.name: Mankey
pokemon.pokedex: It lives in treetop colonies. If one becomes enraged,the whole colony rampages for no reason.

pokemon.name: Primeape
pokemon.pokedex: It is always outrageously furious. If it gives chase,it will tenaciously track the target no matter how far.

pokemon.name: Growlithe
pokemon.pokedex: Extremely loyal,it will fearlessly bark at any opponent to protect its own Trainer from harm.

pokemon.name: Arcanine
pokemon.pokedex: The sight of it running over 6,200 miles in a single day and night has captivated many people.

pokemon.name: Poliwag
pokemon.pokedex: For Poliwag,swimming is easier than walking. The swirl pattern on its belly is actually part of the Pokémon's innards showing through the skin.

pokemon.name: Poliwhirl
pokemon.pokedex: Staring at the swirl on its belly causes drowsiness. This trait of Poliwhirl's has been used in place of lullabies to get children to go to sleep.

pokemon.name: Poliwrath
pokemon.pokedex: Its body is solid muscle. When swimming through cold seas,Poliwrath uses its impressive arms to smash through drift ice and plow forward.

pokemon.name: Abra
pokemon.pokedex: It seems this species of Abra became detached from psychic powers long ago. In spite of this,it still spends most of its time sleeping.

pokemon.name: Kadabra
pokemon.pokedex: It harnesses latent draconic energy throughout the region to channel its attacks,it doesn't appear picky on where the draconic energy comes from.

pokemon.name: Alakazam
pokemon.pokedex: A master of channeling latent energy throughout the region,it carves entire ecosystems energy signatures to its will to help its young learn to channel that power as well.

pokemon.name: Machop
pokemon.pokedex: Its whole body is composed of muscles. Even though it's the size of a human child,it can hurl 100 grown-ups.

pokemon.name: Machoke
pokemon.pokedex: Its formidable body never gets tired. It helps people by doing work such as the moving of heavy goods.

pokemon.name: Machamp
pokemon.pokedex: It quickly swings its four arms to rock its opponents with ceaseless punches and chops from all angles.

pokemon.name: Bellsprout
pokemon.pokedex: Its bud looks like a human face. Because of the bud,it is rumored to be a type of legendary mandrake plant.

pokemon.name: Weepinbell
pokemon.pokedex: It spits out Poison Powder to immobilize the enemy and then finishes it with a spray of Acid.

pokemon.name: Victreebel
pokemon.pokedex: Once ingested into this Pokémon's body,even the hardest object will melt into nothing.

pokemon.name: Tentacool
pokemon.pokedex: This Pokémon is mostly made of water. A Tentacool out in the ocean is very hard to spot,because its body blends in with the sea.

pokemon.name: Tentacruel
pokemon.pokedex: Its 80 tentacles can stretch and shrink freely. Tentacruel ensnares prey in a net of spread-out tentacles,delivering venomous stings to its catch.

pokemon.name: Geodude
pokemon.pokedex: It is impossible to distinguish from rocks. It slams against others in contests of hardness.

pokemon.name: Graveler
pokemon.pokedex: Rolls down slopes to move. It rolls over any obstacle without slowing or changing its direction.

pokemon.name: Golem
pokemon.pokedex: Even dynamite can't harm its hard,boulder-like body. It sheds its hide just once a year.

pokemon.name: Ponyta
pokemon.pokedex: It can't run properly when it's newly born. As it races around with others of its kind,its legs grow stronger.

pokemon.name: Rapidash
pokemon.pokedex: This Pokémon can be seen galloping through fields at speeds of up to 150 mph,its fiery mane fluttering in the wind.

pokemon.name: Slowpoke
pokemon.pokedex: When this Pokémon's tail is soaked in water,sweetness seeps from it. Slowpoke uses this trait to lure in and fish up other Pokémon.

pokemon.name: Slowbro
pokemon.pokedex: Being bitten by a Shellder shocked this Pokémon into standing on two legs. If the Shellder lets go,it seems Slowbro will turn back into a Slowpoke.

pokemon.name: Magnemite
pokemon.pokedex: At times,Magnemite runs out of electricity and ends up on the ground. If you give batteries to a grounded Magnemite,it'll start moving again.

pokemon.name: Magneton
pokemon.pokedex: This Pokémon is three Magnemite that have linked together. Magneton sends out powerful radio waves to study its surroundings.

pokemon.name: Farfetch'd
pokemon.pokedex: They use a plant stalk as a weapon,but not all of them use it in the same way. Several distinct styles of stalk fighting have been observed.

pokemon.name: Doduo
pokemon.pokedex: It mimics a snowman to evade predators. Unfortunately,this usually draws the attention of children.

pokemon.name: Dofrio
pokemon.pokedex: The head in the middle has a very nasty temper,while the head above it is whimsical and carefree.

pokemon.name: Seel
pokemon.pokedex: Covered with light blue fur,its hide is thick and tough. It is active in bitter cold of -40 degrees Fahrenheit.

pokemon.name: Dewgong
pokemon.pokedex: Its streamlined body has little drag in water. The colder the temperature,the friskier it gets.

pokemon.name: Grimer
pokemon.pokedex: Appears in filthy areas. It thrives by sucking up polluted sludge that is pumped out of factories.

pokemon.name: Muk
pokemon.pokedex: A toxic fluid seeps from its body. The fluid instantly kills plants and trees on contact.

pokemon.name: Shellder
pokemon.pokedex: It swims facing backward by opening and closing its two-piece shell. It is surprisingly fast.

pokemon.name: Cloyster
pokemon.pokedex: Its shell is extremely hard. It cannot be shattered,even with a bomb. The shell opens only when it is attacking.

pokemon.name: Gastly
pokemon.pokedex: Its shell is extremely hard. It cannot be shattered,even with a bomb. The shell opens only when it is attacking.

pokemon.name: Haunter
pokemon.pokedex: Its tongue is made of gas. If licked,its victim starts shaking constantly until death eventually comes.

pokemon.name: Gengar
pokemon.pokedex: On the night of a full moon,if shadows move on their own and laugh,it must be Gengar's doing.

pokemon.name: Onix
pokemon.pokedex: It usually lives underground. It searches for food while boring its way through the ground at 50 miles per hour.

pokemon.name: Drowzee
pokemon.pokedex: If you think that you had a good dream but you can't remember it,a Drowzee has probably eaten it.

pokemon.name: Hypno
pokemon.pokedex: Seeing its swinging pendulum can induce sleep in three seconds,even in someone who just woke up.

pokemon.name: Krabby
pokemon.pokedex: If it senses danger approaching,it cloaks itself with bubbles from its mouth so it will look bigger.

pokemon.name: Kingler
pokemon.pokedex: Its large and hard pincer has 10,000-horsepower strength. However,being so big,it is unwieldy to move.

pokemon.name: Voltorb
pokemon.pokedex: Usually found in shrines and caves,it stores heat inside its body to prepare for evolution.

pokemon.name: Electrode
pokemon.pokedex: It stores energy inside its ring,which it then releases violently as blasts of fire. It is considered a crop destroying god in some tribal villages.

pokemon.name: Exeggcute
pokemon.pokedex: These Pokémon get nervous when they're not in a group of six. The minute even one member of the group goes missing,Exeggcute become cowardly.

pokemon.name: Exeggutor
pokemon.pokedex: When they work together,Exeggutor's three heads can put out powerful psychic energy. Cloudy days make this Pokémon sluggish.

pokemon.name: Cubone
pokemon.pokedex: Its mask is hand-carven and gifted to it upon its birth by its parents. It is said those who try to look behind the mask is attacked violently.

pokemon.name: Marowak
pokemon.pokedex: This Pokemon collects its shedded thorns from its back and wraps them into their club,creating a deadly poisonous mace.

pokemon.name: Hitmonlee
pokemon.pokedex: This amazing Pokémon has an awesome sense of balance. It can kick in succession from any position.

pokemon.name: Hitmonchan
pokemon.pokedex: Its punches slice the air. They are launched at such high speed,even a slight graze could cause a burn.

pokemon.name: Lickitung
pokemon.pokedex: Bug Pokémon are Lickitung's main food source. This Pokémon paralyzes its prey with a lick from its long tongue,then swallows the prey whole.

pokemon.name: Koffing
pokemon.pokedex: Far more cruel than its Kantonian counterpart,it is theorized that instead of absorbing toxic fumes to grow,it absorbs spirits.

pokemon.name: Weezing
pokemon.pokedex: It constantly exudes ephemeral gasses from its body. It is said that when someone inhales these gasses,they can see visions of the afterlife.

pokemon.name: Rhyhorn
pokemon.pokedex: Strong,but not too bright,this Pokémon can shatter even a skyscraper with its charging tackles.

pokemon.name: Rhydon
pokemon.pokedex: It begins walking on its hind legs after evolution. It can punch holes through boulders with its horn.

pokemon.name: Chansey
pokemon.pokedex: This species was once very slow. To protect their eggs from other creatures,these Pokémon became able to flee quickly.

pokemon.name: Tangela
pokemon.pokedex: Hidden beneath a tangle of vines that grows nonstop even if the vines are torn off,this Pokémon's true appearance remains a mystery.

pokemon.name: Kangaskhan
pokemon.pokedex: Although it's carrying its baby in a pouch on its belly,Kangaskhan is swift on its feet. It intimidates its opponents with quick jabs.

pokemon.name: Horsea
pokemon.pokedex: They swim with dance-like motions and cause whirlpools to form. Horsea compete to see which of them can generate the biggest whirlpool.

pokemon.name: Seadra
pokemon.pokedex: Seadra's mouth is slender,but its suction power is strong. In an instant,Seadra can suck in food that's larger than the opening of its mouth.

pokemon.name: Goldeen
pokemon.pokedex: Its dorsal,pectoral,and tail fins wave elegantly in water. That is why it is known as the Water Dancer.

pokemon.name: Seaking
pokemon.pokedex: Using its horn,it bores holes in riverbed boulders,making nests to prevent its eggs from washing away.

pokemon.name: Staryu
pokemon.pokedex: Fish Pokémon nibble at it,but Staryu isn't bothered. Its body regenerates quickly,even if part of it is completely torn off.

pokemon.name: Starmie
pokemon.pokedex: Starmie swims by spinning its body at high speed. As this Pokémon cruises through the ocean,it absorbs tiny plankton.

pokemon.name: Jynx
pokemon.pokedex: Behind the unassuming face lies a cold set of teeth,which it uses to catch prey. It can levitate for a short while using a weird power.

pokemon.name: Electabuzz
pokemon.pokedex: Many power plants keep Ground-type Pokémon around as a defense against Electabuzz that come seeking electricity.

pokemon.name: Magmar
pokemon.pokedex: Magmar dispatches its prey with fire. But it regrets this habit once it realizes that it has burned its intended prey to a charred crisp.

pokemon.name: Pinsir
pokemon.pokedex: Its powerful carapace,harder than diamond,lets it shake off even tank shells. The leader of the pack has the most scars on its iron mantle.

pokemon.name: Tauros
pokemon.pokedex: When Tauros begins whipping itself with its tails,it's a warning that the Pokémon is about to charge with astounding speed.

pokemon.name: Magikarp
pokemon.pokedex: Its swimming muscles are weak,so it is easily washed away by currents. In places where water pools,you can see many Magikarp deposited there by the flow.

pokemon.name: Gyarados
pokemon.pokedex: It is an extremely vicious and violent Pokémon. When humans begin to fight,it will appear and burn everything to the ground with intensely hot flames.

pokemon.name: Lapras
pokemon.pokedex: A smart and kindhearted Pokémon,it glides across the surface of the sea while its beautiful song echoes around it.

pokemon.name: Ditto
pokemon.pokedex: It can reconstitute its entire cellular structure to change into what it sees,but it returns to normal when it relaxes.

pokemon.name: Eevee
pokemon.pokedex: Thanks to its unstable genetic makeup,this special Pokémon conceals many different possible evolutions.

pokemon.name: Vaporeon
pokemon.pokedex: Its body's cellular structure is similar to the molecular composition of water. It can melt invisibly in water.

pokemon.name: Jolteon
pokemon.pokedex: If it is angered or startled,the fur all over its body bristles like sharp needles that pierce foes.

pokemon.name: Flareon
pokemon.pokedex: Once it has stored up enough heat,this Pokémon's body temperature can reach up to 1,700 degrees Fahrenheit.

pokemon.name: Porygon
pokemon.pokedex: In recent years,this species has been very helpful in cyberspace. These Pokémon will go around checking to make sure no suspicious data exists.

pokemon.name: Omanyte
pokemon.pokedex: This Pokémon is a member of an ancient,extinct species. Omanyte paddles through water with its 10 tentacles,looking like it's just drifting along.

pokemon.name: Omastar
pokemon.pokedex: Weighed down by a large and heavy shell,Omastar couldn't move very fast. Some say it went extinct because it was unable to catch food.

pokemon.name: Kabuto
pokemon.pokedex: While some say this species has gone extinct,Kabuto sightings are apparently fairly common in some places.

pokemon.name: Kabutops
pokemon.pokedex: The cause behind the extinction of this species is unknown. Kabutops were aggressive Pokémon that inhabited warm seas.

pokemon.name: Aerodactyl
pokemon.pokedex: These Pokemon have existed for thousands of years,as they are as ancient as the forests they protect.

pokemon.name: Snorlax
pokemon.pokedex: For some reason,this Pokemon believes it is the king of the mountain,yet the only thing it does all day is sleep.

pokemon.name: Articuno
pokemon.pokedex: It's said that this Pokémon's beautiful blue wings are made of ice. Articuno flies over snowy mountains,its long tail fluttering along behind it.

pokemon.name: Zapdos
pokemon.pokedex: Zapdos is a legendary bird Pokémon. It's said that when Zapdos rubs its feathers together,lightning will fall immediately after.

pokemon.name: Moltres
pokemon.pokedex: It's one of the legendary bird Pokémon. When Moltres flaps its flaming wings,they glimmer with a dazzling red glow.

pokemon.name: Dratini
pokemon.pokedex: The first instance of Dratini sightings where under a meteor shower,so it is theorized that it came from space.

pokemon.name: Dragonair
pokemon.pokedex: Dragonair passively stores high amounts of energy in its armor,which is released all at once when its about to evolve.

pokemon.name: Dragonite
pokemon.pokedex: On par with legendary Pokemon,most humans spend their entire life not even knowing about their existence. The energy generated by them is otherwordly.

pokemon.name: Mewtwo
pokemon.pokedex: Created from the DNA of Mew,this Pokémon is a dangerous combination of overwhelming power and a savage heart.

pokemon.name: Mew
pokemon.pokedex: It's very intelligent and can use an incredible variety of moves. Many believe that all other Pokémon are descendants of this one.

pokemon.name: Chikorita
pokemon.pokedex: It uses the leaf on its head to determine the temperature and humidity. It loves to sunbathe.

pokemon.name: Bayleef
pokemon.pokedex: The buds that ring its neck give off a spicy aroma that perks people up.

pokemon.name: Meganium
pokemon.pokedex: Meganium's breath has the power to revive dead grass and plants. It can make them healthy again.

pokemon.name: Cyndaquil
pokemon.pokedex: It is said that the ghostly flames spouting from its back burn brighter when specters are nearby.

pokemon.name: Quilava
pokemon.pokedex: Be careful if it turns its back during battle. It means that it will attack with the fire on its back.

pokemon.name: Typhlosion
pokemon.pokedex: It has a secret,devastating move. It rubs its blazing fur together to cause huge explosions.

pokemon.name: Totodile
pokemon.pokedex: Its powerful,well-developed jaws are capable of crushing anything. Even its Trainer must be careful.

pokemon.name: Croconaw
pokemon.pokedex: Once it bites down,it won't let go until it loses its fangs. New fangs quickly grow into place.

pokemon.name: Feraligatr
pokemon.pokedex: When it bites with its massive and powerful jaws,it shakes its head and savagely tears its victim up.

pokemon.name: Sentret
pokemon.pokedex: It stands on its tail so it can see a long way. If it spots an enemy,it cries loudly to warn its kind.

pokemon.name: Furret
pokemon.pokedex: It makes a nest to suit its long and skinny body. The nest is impossible for other Pokémon to enter.

pokemon.name: Hoothoot
pokemon.pokedex: It begins to hoot at the same time every day. Some Trainers use them in place of clocks.

pokemon.name: Noctowl
pokemon.pokedex: Its eyes are specially developed to enable it to see clearly even in murky darkness and minimal light.

pokemon.name: Ledyba
pokemon.pokedex: It is timid and clusters together with others. The fluid secreted by its feet indicates its location.

pokemon.name: Ledian
pokemon.pokedex: The spot patterns on its back grow larger or smaller depending on the number of stars in the night sky.

pokemon.name: Spinarak
pokemon.pokedex: It can blast a blinding light from its back to scare away predators.

pokemon.name: Ariados
pokemon.pokedex: It uses the bright light emanating from its torso to blind its prey before striking.

pokemon.name: Crobat
pokemon.pokedex: Both of its legs have turned into wings. Without a sound,Crobat flies swiftly toward its prey and sinks its fangs into the nape of its target's neck.

pokemon.name: Chinchou
pokemon.pokedex: Its antennae,which evolved from a fin,have both positive and negative charges flowing through them.

pokemon.name: Lanturn
pokemon.pokedex: This Pokémon flashes a bright light that blinds its prey. This creates an opening for it to deliver an electrical attack.

pokemon.name: Pichu
pokemon.pokedex: Despite its small size,it can zap even adult humans. However,if it does so,it also surprises itself.

pokemon.name: Cleffa
pokemon.pokedex: According to local rumors,Cleffa are often seen in places where shooting stars have fallen.

pokemon.name: Igglybuff
pokemon.pokedex: Taking advantage of the softness of its body,Igglybuff moves as if bouncing. Its body turns a deep pink when its temperature rises.

pokemon.name: Togepi
pokemon.pokedex: This rare bird Pokemon hatches at the top of the coldest peaks,as its fire burns bright even at negative temperatures.

pokemon.name: Togetic
pokemon.pokedex: Its highly curious,but its incapability of flying holds it back from exploring new places. Its fire burns bright when its happy.

pokemon.name: Natu
pokemon.pokedex: Because its wings aren't yet fully grown,it has to hop to get around. It is always staring at something.

pokemon.name: Xatu
pokemon.pokedex: They say that it stays still and quiet because it is seeing both the past and future at the same time.

pokemon.name: Mareep
pokemon.pokedex: It stores lots of air in its soft fur,allowing it to stay cool in summer and warm in winter.

pokemon.name: Flaaffy
pokemon.pokedex: If its coat becomes fully charged with electricity,its tail lights up. It fires hair that zaps on impact.

pokemon.name: Ampharos
pokemon.pokedex: The tail's tip shines brightly and can be seen from far away. It acts as a beacon for lost people.

pokemon.name: Bellossom
pokemon.pokedex: Bellossom gather at times and appear to dance. They say that the dance is a ritual to summon the sun.

pokemon.name: Marill
pokemon.pokedex: Even after Marill swims in a cold sea,its water- repellent fur dries almost as soon as Marill leaves the water. That's why this Pokémon is never cold.

pokemon.name: Azumarill
pokemon.pokedex: These Pokémon create air-filled bubbles. When Azurill play in rivers,Azumarill will cover them with these bubbles.

pokemon.name: Sudowoodo
pokemon.pokedex: If a tree branch shakes when there is no wind,it's a Sudowoodo,not a tree. It hides from the rain.

pokemon.name: Politoed
pokemon.pokedex: At nightfall,these Pokémon appear on the shores of lakes. They announce their territorial claims by letting out cries that sound like shouting.

pokemon.name: Hoppip
pokemon.pokedex: The eye motifs on its wings have similar properties to hypnotizing devices. It feeds off of dreams.

pokemon.name: Skiploom
pokemon.pokedex: The "planteye" on top of its head releases a somniferous powder. Those who breathe it in fall into a deep coma.

pokemon.name: Jumpluff
pokemon.pokedex: By flashing bright lights from its limbs,it causes powerful headaches that eventually knock out its opponents. It flies lowly in the night,hunting for people's dreams.

pokemon.name: Aipom
pokemon.pokedex: Its tail is so powerful that it can use it to grab a tree branch and hold itself up in the air.

pokemon.name: Sunkern
pokemon.pokedex: It lives by drinking only dewdrops from under the leaves of plants. It is said that it eats nothing else.

pokemon.name: Sunflora
pokemon.pokedex: It gets energy from warm sunlight and is known for its habit of moving in pursuit of it.

pokemon.name: Yanma
pokemon.pokedex: If it flaps its wings really fast,it can generate shock waves that will shatter windows in the area.

pokemon.name: Wooper
pokemon.pokedex: When walking on land,it covers its body with a poisonous film that keeps its skin from dehydrating.

pokemon.name: Quagsire
pokemon.pokedex: Its body is always slimy. It often bangs its head on the river bottom as it swims but seems not to care.

pokemon.name: Espeon
pokemon.pokedex: It unleashes psychic power from the orb on its forehead. When its power is exhausted,the orb grows dull and dark.

pokemon.name: Umbreon
pokemon.pokedex: When this Pokémon becomes angry,its pores secrete a poisonous sweat,which it sprays at its opponent's eyes.

pokemon.name: Murkrow
pokemon.pokedex: Feared and loathed by many,it is believed to bring misfortune to all those who see it at night.

pokemon.name: Slowking
pokemon.pokedex: Miraculously,this former Slowpoke's latent intelligence was drawn out when Shellder poison raced through its brain.

pokemon.name: Misdreavus
pokemon.pokedex: It likes playing mischievous tricks,such as screaming and wailing to startle people at night.

pokemon.name: Unown
pokemon.pokedex: Shaped like ancient writing,it is a huge mystery whether language or Unown came first.

pokemon.name: Wobbuffet
pokemon.pokedex: To keep its pitch-black tail hidden,it lives quietly in the darkness. It is never first to attack.

pokemon.name: Girafarig
pokemon.pokedex: Its tail has a small brain of its own. Beware! If you get close,it may react to your scent by biting.

pokemon.name: Pineco
pokemon.pokedex: It looks just like a pinecone. Its shell protects it from bird Pokémon that peck it by mistake.

pokemon.name: Forretress
pokemon.pokedex: It remains immovably rooted to its tree. It scatters pieces of its hard shell to drive its enemies away.

pokemon.name: Dunsparce
pokemon.pokedex: It digs into the ground with its tail and makes a mazelike nest. It can fly just a little.

pokemon.name: Gligar
pokemon.pokedex: It flies straight at its target's face,then clamps down on the startled victim to inject poison.

pokemon.name: Steelix
pokemon.pokedex: It is said that if an Onix lives for over 100 years,its composition changes to become diamond-like.

pokemon.name: Snubbull
pokemon.pokedex: Small Pokémon flee from its scary face. It is,however,considered by women to be cute.

pokemon.name: Granbull
pokemon.pokedex: It can make most any Pokémon run away simply by opening its mouth wide to reveal its big fangs.

pokemon.name: Qwilfish
pokemon.pokedex: When faced with a larger opponent,it swallows as much water as it can to match the opponent's size.

pokemon.name: Scizor
pokemon.pokedex: Bulky pincers account for one third of Scizor's body weight. A single swing of one of these pincers will crush a boulder completely.

pokemon.name: Shuckle
pokemon.pokedex: It stores berries inside its shell. To avoid attacks,it hides beneath rocks and remains completely still.

pokemon.name: Heracross
pokemon.pokedex: With its Herculean powers,it can easily throw around an object that is 100 times its own weight.

pokemon.name: Sneasel
pokemon.pokedex: It has a cunning yet savage disposition. It waits for parents to leave their nests,and then it sneaks in to steal their eggs.

pokemon.name: Teddiursa
pokemon.pokedex: Before food becomes scarce in wintertime,its habit is to hoard food in many hidden locations.

pokemon.name: Ursaring
pokemon.pokedex: Although it has a large body,it is quite skilled at climbing trees. It eats and sleeps in the treetops.

pokemon.name: Slugma
pokemon.pokedex: Its body is made of magma. If it doesn't keep moving,its body will cool and harden.

pokemon.name: Magcargo
pokemon.pokedex: Its body is as hot as lava and is always billowing. Flames will occasionally burst from its shell.

pokemon.name: Swinub
pokemon.pokedex: It rubs its snout on the ground to find and dig up food. It sometimes discovers hot springs.

pokemon.name: Piloswine
pokemon.pokedex: If it charges at an enemy,the hairs on its back stand up straight. It is very sensitive to sound.

pokemon.name: Corsola
pokemon.pokedex: It will regrow any branches that break off its head. People keep particularly beautiful Corsola branches as charms to promote safe childbirth.

pokemon.name: Remoraid
pokemon.pokedex: Using its dorsal fin as a suction pad,it clings to a Mantine's underside to scavenge for leftovers.

pokemon.name: Octillery
pokemon.pokedex: It has a tendency to want to be in holes. It prefers rock crags or pots and sprays ink from them before attacking.

pokemon.name: Delibird
pokemon.pokedex: It has a generous habit of sharing its food with people and Pokémon,so it's always scrounging around for more food.

pokemon.name: Mantine
pokemon.pokedex: Mantine lurk in the dunes,and can leap from their hiding spot in a fraction of a second to devour their prey.

pokemon.name: Skarmory
pokemon.pokedex: Wild populations travel in groups lead by a single Skarmonarch who are protected by the Skarmory. They will ward off any invaders without mercy.

pokemon.name: Houndour
pokemon.pokedex: To corner prey,they check each other's location using barks that only they can understand.

pokemon.name: Houndoom
pokemon.pokedex: The flames it breathes when angry contain toxins. If they cause a burn,it will hurt forever.

pokemon.name: Kingdra
pokemon.pokedex: With the arrival of a storm at sea,this Pokémon will show itself on the surface. When a Kingdra and a Dragonite meet,a fierce battle ensues.

pokemon.name: Phanpy
pokemon.pokedex: It is strong despite its compact size. It can easily pick up and carry an adult human on its back.

pokemon.name: Donphan
pokemon.pokedex: An internal organ transmutes the outside moisture into warm water,which acts as a substitute to its blood in extremely cold temperatures.

pokemon.name: Porygon2
pokemon.pokedex: After artificial intelligence was implemented in Porygon2,the Pokémon began using a strange language that only other Porygon2 understand.

pokemon.name: Stantler
pokemon.pokedex: Stantler's magnificent antlers were once traded at high prices as works of art. As a result,this Pokémon was hunted close to extinction.

pokemon.name: Smeargle
pokemon.pokedex: Once it becomes an adult,it has a tendency to let its comrades plant footprints on its back.

pokemon.name: Tyrogue
pokemon.pokedex: Even though it is small,it can't be ignored because it will slug any handy target without warning.

pokemon.name: Hitmontop
pokemon.pokedex: The energy of the Shiny Stone enlightened this Pokemon to never before seen levels of serenity. It is almost impossible to distract.

pokemon.name: Smoochum
pokemon.pokedex: It waltzes around kissing anyone that it comes into contact with,while leaving nasty injuries that look like leech bites.

pokemon.name: Elekid
pokemon.pokedex: It's not good at storing electricity yet. This Pokémon sneaks into people's homes,looking for electrical outlets to eat electricity from.

pokemon.name: Magby
pokemon.pokedex: This Pokémon makes its home near volcanoes. At the end of the day,Magby soaks in magma,resting and recovering from the day's fatigue.

pokemon.name: Miltank
pokemon.pokedex: Miltank produces highly nutritious milk,so it's been supporting the lives of people and other Pokémon since ancient times.

pokemon.name: Blissey
pokemon.pokedex: Blissey lays mysterious eggs that are filled with happiness. It's said that anyone who eats a Blissey egg will start acting kindly to all others.

pokemon.name: Raikou
pokemon.pokedex: It embodies the speed of lightning. Its roars send shock waves shuddering through the air and shake the ground as if lightning bolts had come crashing down.

pokemon.name: Entei
pokemon.pokedex: It embodies the passion of magma. Born in the eruption of a volcano,it can send up massive bursts of fire that consume everything that they touch.

pokemon.name: Suicune
pokemon.pokedex: Suicune embodies the compassion of a pure spring of water. It runs across the land with gracefulness. This Pokémon has the power to purify dirty water.

pokemon.name: Larvitar
pokemon.pokedex: Born deep underground,it comes aboveground and becomes a pupa once it has finished eating the surrounding soil.

pokemon.name: Pupitar
pokemon.pokedex: Even sealed in its shell,it can move freely. Hard and fast,it has outstanding destructive power.

pokemon.name: Tyranitar
pokemon.pokedex: The quakes caused when it walks make even great mountains crumble and change the surrounding terrain.

pokemon.name: Lugia
pokemon.pokedex: It is said to be the guardian of the seas. It is rumored to have been seen on the night of a storm.

pokemon.name: Ho-Oh
pokemon.pokedex: A legend says that its body glows in seven colors. A rainbow is said to form behind it when it flies.

pokemon.name: Celebi
pokemon.pokedex: This Pokémon traveled through time to come from the future. It bolsters grass and trees with its own strength,and it can heal wounds,too.

pokemon.name: Treecko
pokemon.pokedex: Quite skittish,its diet primarily consists of twigs and leaves. It mimetizes with the environment to escape danger.

pokemon.name: Grovyle
pokemon.pokedex: The sheer power gained from evolution changed this Pokemon's metabolism,as it now behaves like an ambush predator.

pokemon.name: Sceptile
pokemon.pokedex: It can adapt to any and all environments,sitting at the top of the food chain. Because of this,they are an invasive species in most areas of the world.

pokemon.name: Torchic
pokemon.pokedex: Their immense ghostly energy allows them to summon additional limbs for a short time,but their inexperience makes them quite clumsy.

pokemon.name: Combusken
pokemon.pokedex: They blend in seemlessly with the shadows,which enable an easy ambush. When ignored,they will sometimes attack their own trainer.

pokemon.name: Blaziken
pokemon.pokedex: Wild and unpredictable,their legs kick the life out of their opponents. The floating limbs disappear if they stray too far from the main body.

pokemon.name: Mudkip
pokemon.pokedex: These Mudkips can be found sleeping soundly under frozen lakes. Their tails connect to the ice above,allowing them to sense vibrations from threats above.

pokemon.name: Marshtomp
pokemon.pokedex: Their icy blankets support their sleeping bodies and provide a shelter for small fish Pokemon. Unfortunately if they wander to close to its snoring mouth they may become a midnight snack.

pokemon.name: Swampert
pokemon.pokedex: Its hibernation can preserve itself for years past the typical life span of a Pokemon its size.

pokemon.name: Poochyena
pokemon.pokedex: It has a very tenacious nature. Its acute sense of smell lets it chase a chosen prey without ever losing track.

pokemon.name: Mightyena
pokemon.pokedex: It chases down prey in a pack of around ten. They defeat foes with perfectly coordinated teamwork.

pokemon.name: Zigzagoon
pokemon.pokedex: It marks its territory by rubbing its bristly fur on trees. This variety of Zigzagoon is friendlier and calmer than the kind native to Galar.

pokemon.name: Linoone
pokemon.pokedex: It uses its explosive speed and razor-sharp claws to bring down prey. Running along winding paths is not its strong suit.

pokemon.name: Wurmple
pokemon.pokedex: It lives among the tall grass and in forests. It repels attacks by raising up the spikes on its rear.

pokemon.name: Silcoon
pokemon.pokedex: It drinks dew that collects on its silk and waits for evolution. Its hard cocoon repels attacks.

pokemon.name: Beautifly
pokemon.pokedex: It has an aggressive nature. It stabs prey with its long,narrow mouth to drain the prey's fluids.

pokemon.name: Cascoon
pokemon.pokedex: It never forgets any attack it endured while in the cocoon. After evolution,it seeks payback.

pokemon.name: Dustox
pokemon.pokedex: It violently flutters its wings to scatter toxic dust when attacked. It becomes active after sunset.

pokemon.name: Lotad
pokemon.pokedex: It searches about for clean water. If it does not drink water for too long,the leaf on its head wilts.

pokemon.name: Lombre
pokemon.pokedex: It lives at the water's edge where it is sunny. It sleeps on a bed of water grass by day and becomes active at night.

pokemon.name: Ludicolo
pokemon.pokedex: The rhythm of bright,festive music activates Ludicolo's cells,making it more powerful.

pokemon.name: Seedot
pokemon.pokedex: It attaches itself to a tree branch using the top of its head. Strong winds can sometimes make it fall.

pokemon.name: Nuzleaf
pokemon.pokedex: It lives deep in forests. With the leaf on its head,it makes a flute whose song makes listeners uneasy.

pokemon.name: Shiftry
pokemon.pokedex: A Pokémon that was feared as a forest guardian. It can read the foe's mind and take preemptive action.

pokemon.name: Taillow
pokemon.pokedex: It dislikes cold seasons. They migrate to other lands in search of warmth,flying over 180 miles a day.

pokemon.name: Swellow
pokemon.pokedex: It dives at a steep angle as soon as it spots its prey. It catches its prey with sharp claws.

pokemon.name: Wingull
pokemon.pokedex: It soars on updrafts without flapping its wings. It makes a nest on sheer cliffs at the sea's edge.

pokemon.name: Pelipper
pokemon.pokedex: Skimming the water's surface,it dips its large bill in the sea,scoops up food and water,and carries it.

pokemon.name: Ralts
pokemon.pokedex: Its black plumage is said to bring misfortune to others near it.

pokemon.name: Kirlia
pokemon.pokedex: It uses wind currents to dance about in the night sky,even while hunting.

pokemon.name: Gardevoir
pokemon.pokedex: It has a latent power to read minds. A folktale tells that,long ago,this Pokemon and its "mirrored image" served a malicious king.

pokemon.name: Surskit
pokemon.pokedex: It appears as if it is skating on water. It draws prey with a sweet scent from the tip of its head.

pokemon.name: Masquerain
pokemon.pokedex: It flaps its four wings to hover and fly freely in any direction--to and fro and sideways.

pokemon.name: Shroomish
pokemon.pokedex: It spouts poison spores from the top of its head. These spores cause pain all over if inhaled.

pokemon.name: Breloom
pokemon.pokedex: It scatters poisonous spores and throws powerful punches while its foe is hampered by inhaled spores.

pokemon.name: Slakoth
pokemon.pokedex: If it eats just three leaves in a day,it is satisfied. Other than that,it sleeps for 20 hours a day.

pokemon.name: Vigoroth
pokemon.pokedex: Its stress level rises if it cannot keep moving constantly. Too much stress makes it feel sick.

pokemon.name: Slaking
pokemon.pokedex: It is the world's most slothful Pokémon. However,it can exert horrifying power by releasing pent-up energy all at once.

pokemon.name: Nincada
pokemon.pokedex: It can sometimes live underground for more than 10 years. It absorbs nutrients from the roots of trees.

pokemon.name: Ninjask
pokemon.pokedex: Its cry leaves a lasting headache if heard for too long. It moves so quickly that it is almost invisible.

pokemon.name: Shedinja
pokemon.pokedex: A strange Pokémon. It flies without moving its wings,has a hollow shell for a body,and does not breathe.

pokemon.name: Whismur
pokemon.pokedex: When Whismur cries,the sound of its own voice startles it,making the Pokémon cry even louder. It cries until it's exhausted,then it falls asleep.

pokemon.name: Loudred
pokemon.pokedex: The force of this Pokémon's loud voice isn't just the sound. It's also the wave of air pressure that blows opponents away and damages them.

pokemon.name: Exploud
pokemon.pokedex: This Pokémon can do more than just shout. To communicate with others of its kind,it'll emit all sorts of sounds from the holes in its body.

pokemon.name: Makuhita
pokemon.pokedex: It grows stronger by enduring harsh training. It is a gutsy Pokémon that can withstand any attack.

pokemon.name: Hariyama
pokemon.pokedex: It loves to match power with big-bodied Pokémon. It can knock a truck flying with its arm thrusts.

pokemon.name: Azurill
pokemon.pokedex: Although Azurill are normally docile,an angry one will swing around the big ball on its tail and try to smash its opponents.

pokemon.name: Nosepass
pokemon.pokedex: Its magnetic nose consistently faces north. Travelers check Nosepass to get their bearings.

pokemon.name: Skitty
pokemon.pokedex: Skitty stalk and jump out at unsuspecting travelers from the shadows,terrifying them. In truth,they are very lonely.

pokemon.name: Delcatty
pokemon.pokedex: Delcatty were once scorned as an omen of misfortune. However,in recent times,perception of them has changed,with them now being considered deeply dependable companions.

pokemon.name: Sableye
pokemon.pokedex: This Pokémon is feared. When its gemstone eyes begin to glow with a sinister shine,it's believed that Sableye will steal people's spirits away.

pokemon.name: Mawile
pokemon.pokedex: It chomps with its gaping mouth. Its huge jaws are actually steel horns that have been transformed.

pokemon.name: Aron
pokemon.pokedex: When Aron evolves,it leaves behind molten pebbles. In ancient times,people would collect Aron's shed rocks to warm themselves.

pokemon.name: Lairon
pokemon.pokedex: During territorial disputes,Lairon emits high amounts of steam. Close inspection of their magma armor reveals scratches and dents.

pokemon.name: Aggron
pokemon.pokedex: The temperature inside Aggron's core can be compared to that of an industrial furnace. When threatened,it blows molten rock out of the pores on its back.

pokemon.name: Meditite
pokemon.pokedex: It eats just one berry a day. By enduring hunger,its spirit is tempered and made sharper.

pokemon.name: Medicham
pokemon.pokedex: Through yoga training,it gained the psychic power to predict its foe's next move.

pokemon.name: Electrike
pokemon.pokedex: It stores electricity in its fur. It gives off sparks from all over its body in seasons when the air is dry.

pokemon.name: Manectric
pokemon.pokedex: It stimulates its own muscles with electricity,so it can move quickly. It eases its soreness with electricity,too,so it can recover quickly as well.

pokemon.name: Plusle
pokemon.pokedex: It cheerfully spurs its friends on. The flames on its body shimmer and grow as it moves.

pokemon.name: Minun
pokemon.pokedex: It hates seeing its friends get hurt. The water on its body glimmers in tandem with its mood.

pokemon.name: Volbeat
pokemon.pokedex: It lives around clean ponds. At night,its rear lights up. It converses with others by flashing its light.

pokemon.name: Illumise
pokemon.pokedex: With its sweet aroma,it guides Volbeat to draw signs with light in the night sky.

pokemon.name: Roselia
pokemon.pokedex: If threatened,it will barrage its opponent with heavy blows from its rock-solid arms,which are also full of toxins.

pokemon.name: Gulpin
pokemon.pokedex: There is nothing its stomach can't digest. While it is digesting,vile,overpowering gases are expelled.

pokemon.name: Swalot
pokemon.pokedex: It gulps anything that fits in its mouth. Its special enzymes can dissolve anything.

pokemon.name: Carvanha
pokemon.pokedex: It won't attack while it's alone,not even if it spots prey. Instead,it waits for other Carvanha to join it,and then the Pokémon attack as a group.

pokemon.name: Sharpedo
pokemon.pokedex: As soon as it catches the scent of prey,Sharpedo will jet seawater from its backside,hurtling toward the target to attack at 75 mph.

pokemon.name: Wailmer
pokemon.pokedex: It shows off by spraying jets of seawater from the nostrils above its eyes. It eats a solid ton of Wishiwashi every day.

pokemon.name: Wailord
pokemon.pokedex: Its immense size is the reason for its popularity. Wailord watching is a favorite sightseeing activity in various parts of the world.

pokemon.name: Numel
pokemon.pokedex: Ayreian Numel are rather peaceful Pokemon that get along well with others. However in a battle,the spores they spread are so potent that trainers are advised to protect their mouths and noses to avoid breathing any.

pokemon.name: Camellum
pokemon.pokedex: Recent studies have found that these Pokémon have the ability to communicate with each other through the spores they spread through a network hypothesized to be larger than the region itself.

pokemon.name: Torkoal
pokemon.pokedex: It burns coal inside its shell for energy. It blows out black soot if it is endangered.

pokemon.name: Spoink
pokemon.pokedex: It bounces around on its tail to keep its heart pumping. It carries a pearl from Clamperl on its head.

pokemon.name: Grumpig
pokemon.pokedex: It uses black pearls to amplify its psychic power. It does an odd dance to gain control over foes.

pokemon.name: Spinda
pokemon.pokedex: The chances of two Spinda having identical spot patterns is less than one in four billion.

pokemon.name: Trapinch
pokemon.pokedex: While it may look weak in this larva form,it can shoot devastatingly powerful toxins from its mouth,used as a defense mechanism until evolution.

pokemon.name: Vibrava
pokemon.pokedex: The loss in power during this phase has changed Vibrava's metabolism,now only feeding on plants. They are very skittish and will most likely flee when threatened.

pokemon.name: Flygon
pokemon.pokedex: Most active at night,their wings reflect the moon's light,attracting prey. The poor victim is dissolved into a puddle by this Pokemon's powerful poison and quickly digested.

pokemon.name: Cacnea
pokemon.pokedex: It prefers harsh environments such as deserts. It can survive for 30 days on water stored in its body.

pokemon.name: Cacturne
pokemon.pokedex: Packs of them follow travelers through the desert until the travelers can no longer move.

pokemon.name: Swablu
pokemon.pokedex: Its cottony wings are full of air,making them light and fluffy to the touch. Swablu takes diligent care of its wings.

pokemon.name: Altaria
pokemon.pokedex: This Pokémon has a kind disposition,but if it's provoked,it will threaten opponents with shrill cries before attacking them without mercy.

pokemon.name: Zangoose
pokemon.pokedex: Its fur would all stand on end if it smelled a Seviper nearby. Its sharp claws tear up its foes.

pokemon.name: Seviper
pokemon.pokedex: Constant polishing makes the edge of the blade on its tail extremely sharp. It's Zangoose's archrival.

pokemon.name: Lunatone
pokemon.pokedex: Different types of music can be heard coming from it,depending on the mood it's in.

pokemon.name: Solrock
pokemon.pokedex: Solar energy is the source of its power,so it is strong during the daytime. When it spins,its body shines.

pokemon.name: Barboach
pokemon.pokedex: Its slimy body is hard to grasp. In one region,it is said to have been born from hardened mud.

pokemon.name: Whiscash
pokemon.pokedex: It makes its nest at the bottom of swamps. It will eat anything. If it is alive,Whiscash will eat it.

pokemon.name: Corphish
pokemon.pokedex: No matter how dirty the water in the river,it will adapt and thrive. It has a strong will to survive.

pokemon.name: Crawdaunt
pokemon.pokedex: A brutish Pokémon that loves to battle. It will crash itself into any foe that approaches its nest.

pokemon.name: Baltoy
pokemon.pokedex: It was discovered in ancient ruins. While moving,it constantly spins. It stands on one foot even when asleep.

pokemon.name: Claydol
pokemon.pokedex: It appears to have been born from clay dolls made by ancient people. It uses telekinesis to float and move.

pokemon.name: Lileep
pokemon.pokedex: This Pokémon was restored from a fossil. Lileep once lived in warm seas that existed approximately 100,000,000 years ago.

pokemon.name: Cradily
pokemon.pokedex: It has short legs and can't walk very fast,but its neck and tentacles can extend to over three times their usual length to nab distant prey.

pokemon.name: Anorith
pokemon.pokedex: Anorith can swim swiftly by pulling its eight wings through the water like oars on a boat. This Pokémon is an ancestor of modern bug Pokémon.

pokemon.name: Armaldo
pokemon.pokedex: After evolution,this Pokémon emerged onto land. Its lower body has become stronger,and blows from its tail are devastating.

pokemon.name: Feebas
pokemon.pokedex: Although unattractive and unpopular,this Pokémon's marvelous vitality has made it a subject of research.

pokemon.name: Milotic
pokemon.pokedex: Milotic has provided inspiration to many artists. It has even been referred to as the most beautiful Pokémon of all.

pokemon.name: Castform
pokemon.pokedex: It has the ability to change its form into the sun,the rain,or a snow cloud,depending on the weather.

pokemon.name: Kecleon
pokemon.pokedex: It changes its shading to match its surroundings so it can sneak up on prey. Only its belly patterns stay fixed.

pokemon.name: Shuppet
pokemon.pokedex: It loves vengeful emotions and hangs in rows under the eaves of houses where vengeful people live.

pokemon.name: Banette
pokemon.pokedex: Strong feelings of hatred turned a puppet into a Pokémon. If it opens its mouth,its cursed energy escapes.

pokemon.name: Duskull
pokemon.pokedex: If it finds bad children who won't listen to their parents,it will spirit them away ... or so it's said.

pokemon.name: Dusclops
pokemon.pokedex: It seeks drifting will-o'-the-wisps and sucks them into its empty body. What happens inside is a mystery.

pokemon.name: Tropius
pokemon.pokedex: A solitary Pokemon that resides in the depths of the jungle. It utilises powerful wingbeats to both fly and spread seeds,assisting the growth of its home.

pokemon.name: Chimecho
pokemon.pokedex: Emitting ultrasonic cries,it floats on winds to travel great distances.

pokemon.name: Absol
pokemon.pokedex: Records released to the public just after the war state that Absol instinctively punished those that would bring harm to the forests near the conflict.

pokemon.name: Wynaut
pokemon.pokedex: It tends to move in a pack. Individuals squash against one another to toughen their spirits.

pokemon.name: Snorunt
pokemon.pokedex: It attaches itself to the ceiling of volcanic caves to absorb heat,which it then releases to fly around.

pokemon.name: Glalie
pokemon.pokedex: It can shoot concentrated energy waves from its horns. Its fire burns with a bright blue when it's enraged.

pokemon.name: Spheal
pokemon.pokedex: This Pokémon's body is covered in blubber and impressively round. It's faster for Spheal to roll around than walk.

pokemon.name: Sealeo
pokemon.pokedex: This Pokémon has a habit of spinning round things on its nose,whether those things are Poké Balls or Spheal.

pokemon.name: Walrein
pokemon.pokedex: Walrein's tusks keep growing throughout its life. Tusks broken in battle will grow back to their usual impressive size in a year.

pokemon.name: Clamperl
pokemon.pokedex: It is protected by a sturdy shell. Once in a lifetime,it makes a magnificent pearl.

pokemon.name: Huntail
pokemon.pokedex: It lives deep in the sea. With a tail shaped like a small fish,it attracts unsuspecting prey.

pokemon.name: Gorebyss
pokemon.pokedex: Its swimming form is exquisitely elegant. With its thin mouth,it feeds on seaweed that grows between rocks.

pokemon.name: Relicanth
pokemon.pokedex: Said to be an incredibly old species gone extinct,a few specimen have begun appearing near the shores of Ayrei. They look lifeless at a glance.

pokemon.name: Luvdisc
pokemon.pokedex: It floats about pretending to be dead,waiting for its prey to approach before attacking.

pokemon.name: Bagon
pokemon.pokedex: Bagon is a solitary Pokémon that doesn't form groups with others of its kind. It also has a head hard enough to cleave a boulder in one strike.

pokemon.name: Shelgon
pokemon.pokedex: Shelgon ignores its hunger entirely,never eating any food. Apparently,Shelgon will evolve once all its energy stores are used up.

pokemon.name: Salamence
pokemon.pokedex: While basking in the joy of flight generally keeps it in high spirits,it turns into an uncontrollable menace if something angers it.

pokemon.name: Beldum
pokemon.pokedex: From its rear,Beldum emits a magnetic force that rapidly pulls opponents in. They get skewered on Beldum's sharp claws.

pokemon.name: Metang
pokemon.pokedex: Using magnetic forces to stay aloft,this Pokémon flies at high speeds,weaving through harsh mountain terrain in pursuit of prey.

pokemon.name: Metagross
pokemon.pokedex: Metagross is the result of the fusion of two Metang. This Pokémon defeats its opponents through use of its supercomputer-level brain.

pokemon.name: Regirock
pokemon.pokedex: Cutting-edge technology was used to study the internals of this Pokémon's rock body. However,nothing was found,not even brain or a heart.

pokemon.name: Regice
pokemon.pokedex: With cold air that can reach temperatures as low as -328 degrees Fahrenheit,Regice instantly freezes any creature that approaches it.

pokemon.name: Registeel
pokemon.pokedex: It's rumored that this Pokémon was born deep underground in the planet's mantle and that it emerged onto the surface 10,000 years ago.

pokemon.name: Latias
pokemon.pokedex: It is highly sensitive to the emotions of people. If it senses any hostility,it ruffles the feathers all over its body and cries shrilly to intimidate the foe.

pokemon.name: Latios
pokemon.pokedex: Latios has the ability to make others see an image of what it has seen or imagines in its head. This Pokémon is intelligent and understands human speech.

pokemon.name: Kyogre
pokemon.pokedex: Kyogre is said to be the personification of the sea itself. Legends tell of its many clashes against Groudon,as each sought to gain the power of nature.

pokemon.name: Groudon
pokemon.pokedex: Groudon is said to be the personification of the land itself. Legends tell of its many clashes against Kyogre,as each sought to gain the power of nature.

pokemon.name: Rayquaza
pokemon.pokedex: Rayquaza is said to have lived for hundreds of millions of years. Legends remain of how it put to rest the clash between Kyogre and Groudon.

pokemon.name: Jirachi
pokemon.pokedex: It is said to have the ability to grant any wish for just one week every thousand years.

pokemon.name: Deoxys
pokemon.pokedex: DNA from a space virus mutated and became a Pokémon. It appears where auroras are seen.

pokemon.name: Turtwig
pokemon.pokedex: It undertakes photosynthesis with its body,making oxygen. The leaf on its head wilts if it is thirsty.

pokemon.name: Grotle
pokemon.pokedex: It knows where pure water wells up. It carries fellow Pokémon there on its back.

pokemon.name: Torterra
pokemon.pokedex: Small Pokémon occasionally gather on its unmoving back to begin building their nests.

pokemon.name: Chimchar
pokemon.pokedex: A Pokemon with a highly rowdy and unruly disposition,it frequently harasses travelers that enter its territory. However this behavior is not done out of malice,and instead out of curiosity.

pokemon.name: Monferno
pokemon.pokedex: It uses the poison on its tail both in combat and to mark its territory. It frequently gets into territorial disputes with Grafaiai.

pokemon.name: Infernape
pokemon.pokedex: The noxious fumes this pokemon is constantly emitting slows down and disorients its opponents. This in combination with Infernape's blinding speed make it a force to be reckoned with. Its immense speed is a point of pride for this Pokemon,so much so that when it meets an opponent faster than it,it sulks for days on end.

pokemon.name: Piplup
pokemon.pokedex: Because it is very proud,it hates accepting food from people. Its thick down guards it from cold.

pokemon.name: Prinplup
pokemon.pokedex: It lives a solitary life. Its wings deliver wicked blows that can snap even the thickest of trees.

pokemon.name: Empoleon
pokemon.pokedex: The three horns that extend from its beak attest to its power. The leader has the biggest horns.

pokemon.name: Starly
pokemon.pokedex: They flock in great numbers. Though small,they flap their wings with great power.

pokemon.name: Staravia
pokemon.pokedex: It flies around forests and fields in search of bug Pokémon. It stays within a huge flock.

pokemon.name: Staraptor
pokemon.pokedex: It has a savage nature. It will courageously challenge foes that are much larger.

pokemon.name: Bidoof
pokemon.pokedex: It constantly gnaws on logs and rocks to whittle down its front teeth. It nests alongside water.

pokemon.name: Bibarel
pokemon.pokedex: It makes its nest by damming streams with bark and mud. It is known as an industrious worker.

pokemon.name: Kricketot
pokemon.pokedex: When its antennae hit each other,it sounds like the music of a xylophone.

pokemon.name: Kricketune
pokemon.pokedex: It signals its emotions with its melodies. Scientists are studying these melodic patterns.

pokemon.name: Shinx
pokemon.pokedex: This Pokémon generates electricity by contracting its muscles. Excited trembling is a sign that Shinx is generating a tremendous amount of electricity.

pokemon.name: Luxio
pokemon.pokedex: Upon encountering an opponent,this Pokémon prepares for battle by extending its claws,which can put out 1,000,000 volts of electricity.

pokemon.name: Luxray
pokemon.pokedex: Seeing through solid objects uses up a lot of Luxray's electricity,so the Pokémon sleeps for long periods of time to store up energy.

pokemon.name: Budew
pokemon.pokedex: The hardened shell in front of its face protects its otherwise frail body from attacks. It's very rare,as it usually buries in the ground to gather nutrients.

pokemon.name: Roserade
pokemon.pokedex: The serrated fangs on both arms are filled to the brim with quick acting poison. It catches prey with agile movements and injects lethal toxins.

pokemon.name: Cranidos
pokemon.pokedex: A lifelong jungle dweller from 100 million years ago,it would snap obstructing trees with headbutts.

pokemon.name: Rampardos
pokemon.pokedex: Its skull is as hard as iron. It is a brute that tears down jungle trees while catching prey.

pokemon.name: Shieldon
pokemon.pokedex: It was generated from a fossil dug out of a layer of clay that was older than anyone knows. It has a sturdy face.

pokemon.name: Bastiodon
pokemon.pokedex: Any frontal attack is repulsed. It is a docile Pokémon that feeds on grass and berries.

pokemon.name: Burmy
pokemon.pokedex: If its cloak is broken in battle,it quickly remakes the cloak with materials nearby.

pokemon.name: Wormadam
pokemon.pokedex: When Burmy evolved,its cloak became a part of this Pokémon's body. The cloak is never shed.

pokemon.name: Mothim
pokemon.pokedex: It flutters around at night and steals honey from the Combee hive.

pokemon.name: Combee
pokemon.pokedex: The members of the trio spend all their time together. Each one has a slightly different taste in nectar.

pokemon.name: Vespiquen
pokemon.pokedex: It skillfully commands its grubs in battles with its enemies. The grubs are willing to risk their lives to defend Vespiquen.

pokemon.name: Pachirisu
pokemon.pokedex: The two sides of Pachirisu are a perfect parallel to each other. While the pale side is sluggish and lethargic,the other is hyperactive and dangerous.

pokemon.name: Buizel
pokemon.pokedex: It inflates the flotation sac around its neck and pokes its head out of the water to see what is going on.

pokemon.name: Floatzel
pokemon.pokedex: Its flotation sac developed as a result of pursuing aquatic prey. It can double as a rubber raft.

pokemon.name: Cherubi
pokemon.pokedex: It nimbly dashes about to avoid getting pecked by bird Pokémon that would love to make off with its small,nutrient-rich storage ball.

pokemon.name: Cherrim
pokemon.pokedex: The faint scent that emanates from its full blossom entices bug Pokémon to it.

pokemon.name: Shellos
pokemon.pokedex: This Pokémon's habitat shapes its physique. According to some theories,life in warm ocean waters causes this variation to develop.

pokemon.name: Gastrodon
pokemon.pokedex: It secretes a purple fluid to deter enemies. This fluid isn't poisonous. Instead,it's super sticky,and once it sticks,it's very hard to unstick.

pokemon.name: Ambipom
pokemon.pokedex: To eat,it deftly shucks nuts with its two tails. It rarely uses its arms now.

pokemon.name: Drifloon
pokemon.pokedex: They are very fond of people and the positivity they can express. They are often found parading large festivals and parties.

pokemon.name: Drifblim
pokemon.pokedex: This Pokemon always radiates with bright colors. Lost travelers or adventurers who follow it always find their way home.

pokemon.name: Buneary
pokemon.pokedex: Buneary can attack by rolling up their ears and then striking with the force created by unrolling them. This attack becomes stronger with training.

pokemon.name: Lopunny
pokemon.pokedex: Once hot seasons are over,Lopunny's coat will be replaced with fur that holds a lot of insulating air in preparation for colder weather.

pokemon.name: Mismagius
pokemon.pokedex: Its cries sound like incantations to torment the foe. It appears where you least expect it.

pokemon.name: Honchkrow
pokemon.pokedex: Becoming active at night,it is known to swarm with numerous Murkrow in tow.

pokemon.name: Glameow
pokemon.pokedex: When it's happy,Glameow demonstrates beautiful movements of its tail,like a dancing ribbon.

pokemon.name: Purugly
pokemon.pokedex: To make itself appear intimidatingly beefy,it tightly cinches its waist with its twin tails.

pokemon.name: Chingling
pokemon.pokedex: There is an orb inside its mouth. When it hops,the orb bounces all over and makes a ringing sound.

pokemon.name: Stunky
pokemon.pokedex: From its rear,it sprays a foul-smelling liquid at opponents. It aims for their faces,and it can hit them from over 16 feet away.

pokemon.name: Skuntank
pokemon.pokedex: In its belly,it reserves stinky fluid that it shoots from its tail during battle. As this Pokémon's diet varies,so does the stench of its fluid.

pokemon.name: Bronzor
pokemon.pokedex: Polishing Bronzor to a shine makes its surface reflect the truth,according to common lore. Be that as it may,Bronzor hates being polished.

pokemon.name: Bronzong
pokemon.pokedex: Some believe it to be a deity that summons rain clouds. When angered,it lets out a warning cry that rings out like the tolling of a bell.

pokemon.name: Bonsly
pokemon.pokedex: It expels both sweat and tears from its eyes. The sweat is a little salty,while the tears have a slight bitterness.

pokemon.name: Mime Jr.
pokemon.pokedex: It mimics everyone it sees,but it puts extra effort into copying the graceful dance steps of Mr. Rime as practice.

pokemon.name: Happiny
pokemon.pokedex: Happiny's willing to lend its precious round stone to those it's friendly with,but if the stone isn't returned,Happiny will cry and throw a tantrum.

pokemon.name: Chatot
pokemon.pokedex: It can learn and speak human words. If they gather,they all learn the same saying.

pokemon.name: Spiritomb
pokemon.pokedex: All Spiritomb's mischief and misdeeds compelled a traveler to use a mysterious spell to bind Spiritomb to an odd keystone.

pokemon.name: Gible
pokemon.pokedex: Gible attacks anything that moves,and it drags whatever it catches into the crevice that is its lair. Despite the big mouth,Gible's stomach is small.

pokemon.name: Gabite
pokemon.pokedex: Jewels are buried in the caves these Pokémon nest in,but you'll be torn apart by claws and fangs the moment you enter one of these caves.

pokemon.name: Garchomp
pokemon.pokedex: Garchomp makes its home in volcanic mountains. It flies through the sky as fast as a jet airplane,hunting down as much prey as it can.

pokemon.name: Munchlax
pokemon.pokedex: It feels immense joy from harassing others. You'll often find them in the wild,throwing rocks or snow at people and Pokemon.

pokemon.name: Riolu
pokemon.pokedex: Still new to the concept of Cyberspace,this Pokemon is the bioproduct of superfluous files from Lucario.

pokemon.name: Lucario
pokemon.pokedex: By controlling the virtual realm,it can mess with its opponent's data values. However,a virus may find its way inside Lucario when its guard is down.

pokemon.name: Hippopotas
pokemon.pokedex: It moves through the sands with its mouth open,swallowing sand along with its prey. It gets rid of the sand by spouting it from its nose.

pokemon.name: Hippowdon
pokemon.pokedex: Stones can get stuck in the ports on their bodies. Dwebble help dislodge such stones,so Hippowdon look after these Pokémon.

pokemon.name: Skorupi
pokemon.pokedex: After burrowing into the sand,it waits patiently for prey to come near. This Pokémon and Sizzlipede share common descent.

pokemon.name: Drapion
pokemon.pokedex: Its poison is potent,but it rarely sees use. This Pokémon prefers to use physical force instead,going on rampages with its car-crushing strength.

pokemon.name: Croagunk
pokemon.pokedex: Once diluted,its poison becomes medicinal. This Pokémon came into popularity after a pharmaceutical company chose it as a mascot.

pokemon.name: Toxicroak
pokemon.pokedex: It bounces toward opponents and gouges them with poisonous claws. No more than a scratch is needed to knock out its adversaries.

pokemon.name: Carnivine
pokemon.pokedex: It binds itself to trees in marshes. It attracts prey with its sweet-smelling drool and gulps them down.

pokemon.name: Finneon
pokemon.pokedex: After long exposure to sunlight,the patterns on its tail fins shine vividly when darkness arrives.

pokemon.name: Lumineon
pokemon.pokedex: To avoid detection by predators,it crawls along the seafloor using the two fins on its chest.

pokemon.name: Mantyke
pokemon.pokedex: It burrows underground and shocks it's enemy from below as a surprise attack.

pokemon.name: Snover
pokemon.pokedex: It lives on snowy mountains. It sinks its legs into the snow to absorb water and keep its own temperature down.

pokemon.name: Abomasnow
pokemon.pokedex: If it sees any packs of Darumaka going after Snover,it chases them off,swinging its sizable arms like hammers.

pokemon.name: Weavile
pokemon.pokedex: They attack their quarry in packs. Prey as large as Mamoswine easily fall to the teamwork of a group of Weavile.

pokemon.name: Magnezone
pokemon.pokedex: Some say that Magnezone receives signals from space via the antenna on its head and that it's being controlled by some mysterious being.

pokemon.name: Lickilicky
pokemon.pokedex: Lickilicky can do just about anything with its tongue,which is as dexterous as the human hand. In contrast,Lickilicky's use of its fingers is clumsy.

pokemon.name: Rhyperior
pokemon.pokedex: It can load up to three projectiles per arm into the holes in its hands. What launches out of those holes could be either rocks or Roggenrola.

pokemon.name: Tangrowth
pokemon.pokedex: Vine growth is accelerated for Tangrowth living in warm climates. If the vines grow long,Tangrowth shortens them by tearing parts of them off.

pokemon.name: Electivire
pokemon.pokedex: In terms of electrical-energy output,Electivire is one of the best among all Electric Pokémon. It discharges high-voltage currents from its tails.

pokemon.name: Magmortar
pokemon.pokedex: When Magmortar inhales deeply,the fire burning in its belly intensifies,rising in temperature to over 3,600 degrees Fahrenheit.

pokemon.name: Togekiss
pokemon.pokedex: These Pokémon are never seen anywhere near conflict or turmoil. In recent times,they've hardly been seen at all.

pokemon.name: Yanmega
pokemon.pokedex: This six-legged Pokémon is easily capable of transporting an adult in flight. The wings on its tail help it stay balanced.

pokemon.name: Leafeon
pokemon.pokedex: Galarians favor the distinctive aroma that drifts from this Pokémon's leaves. There's a popular perfume made using that scent.

pokemon.name: Glaceon
pokemon.pokedex: The coldness emanating from Glaceon causes powdery snow to form,making it quite a popular Pokémon at ski resorts.

pokemon.name: Gliscor
pokemon.pokedex: Its flight is soundless. It uses its lengthy tail to carry off its prey. Then its elongated fangs do the rest.

pokemon.name: Mamoswine
pokemon.pokedex: It looks strong,and that's exactly what it is. As the weather grows colder,its ice tusks grow longer,thicker,and more impressive.

pokemon.name: Porygon-Z
pokemon.pokedex: Porygon-Z had a program installed to allow it to move between dimensions,but the program also caused instability in Porygon-Z's behavior.

pokemon.name: Gallade
pokemon.pokedex: With its latent powers,it can force anyone to do its bidding. A folktale tells that,long ago,this Pokemon and its "mirrored image" served a malicious king.

pokemon.name: Gyropass
pokemon.pokedex: It rotates endlessly. This behavior has made it the subject of many theories.

pokemon.name: Dusknoir
pokemon.pokedex: With the mouth on its belly,Dusknoir swallows its target whole. The soul is the only thing eaten. Dusknoir disgorges the body before departing.

pokemon.name: Froslass
pokemon.pokedex: It can be seen regularly taking command of others. However,it prefers to work with its likeminded counterpart.

pokemon.name: Rotom
pokemon.pokedex: One boy's invention led to the development of many different machines that take advantage of Rotom's unique capabilities.

pokemon.name: Uxie
pokemon.pokedex: Known as "The Being of Knowledge." It is said that it can wipe out the memory of those who see its eyes.

pokemon.name: Mesprit
pokemon.pokedex: Known as "The Being of Emotion." It taught humans the nobility of sorrow,pain,and joy.

pokemon.name: Azelf
pokemon.pokedex: Known as "The Being of Willpower." It sleeps at the bottom of a lake to keep the world in balance.

pokemon.name: Dialga
pokemon.pokedex: A Pokémon spoken of in legend. It is said that time began moving when Dialga was born.

pokemon.name: Palkia
pokemon.pokedex: It is said to live in a gap in the spatial dimension parallel to ours. It appears in mythology.

pokemon.name: Heatran
pokemon.pokedex: It dwells in volcanic caves. It digs in with its cross-shaped feet to crawl on ceilings and walls.

pokemon.name: Regigigas
pokemon.pokedex: It is said to have made Pokémon that look like itself from a special ice mountain,rocks,and magma.

pokemon.name: Giratina
pokemon.pokedex: This Pokémon is said to live in a world on the reverse side of ours,where common knowledge is distorted and strange.

pokemon.name: Cresselia
pokemon.pokedex: Those who sleep holding Cresselia's feather are assured of joyful dreams. It is said to represent the crescent moon.

pokemon.name: Phione
pokemon.pokedex: It drifts in warm seas. It always returns to where it was born,no matter how far it may have drifted.

pokemon.name: Manaphy
pokemon.pokedex: It starts its life with a wondrous power that permits it to bond with any kind of Pokémon.

pokemon.name: Darkrai
pokemon.pokedex: It can lull people to sleep and make them dream. It is active during nights of the new moon.

pokemon.name: Shaymin
pokemon.pokedex: The blooming of Gracidea flowers confers the power of flight upon it. Feelings of gratitude are the message it delivers.

pokemon.name: Arceus
pokemon.pokedex: It is told in mythology that this Pokémon was born before the universe even existed.

pokemon.name: Victini
pokemon.pokedex: This Pokémon brings victory. It is said that Trainers with Victini always win,regardless of the type of encounter.

pokemon.name: Snivy
pokemon.pokedex: When they're in good health,the liquid metal they cover themselves with doesn't stick to surfaces.

pokemon.name: Servine
pokemon.pokedex: The liquid metal its body is made of is so dense that its an incredibly heavy Pokemon,despite its minute size.

pokemon.name: Serperior
pokemon.pokedex: Its body is made up by more than 85% of liquid metal. To protect itself,it slowly exhales a noxious gas,even while sleeping.

pokemon.name: Tepig
pokemon.pokedex: It can be seen sleeping soundly in lava lakes. It is thought that Tepig are born whenever a volcano erupts.

pokemon.name: Pignite
pokemon.pokedex: The black smoke Pignite is constantly emitting serves both as a way to disorient its opponents and as protection for its body.

pokemon.name: Emboar
pokemon.pokedex: Ayreian Emboar use brute force to claim massive territories to rule over. Territorial disputes between two Emboar only end in scorched earth and ruin.

pokemon.name: Oshawott
pokemon.pokedex: This Pokémon endlessly picks fights with opponents tougher than itself. It has a strong sense of honor.

pokemon.name: Dewott
pokemon.pokedex: Since evolving,it's feather dual blades are now capable of cutting through solid steel with ease.

pokemon.name: Samurott
pokemon.pokedex: It can cut through clouds with one swing of its sword,the territory of this Pokémon is identifiable by looking up and seeing a scarred horizon.

pokemon.name: Patrat
pokemon.pokedex: Extremely cautious,one of them will always be on the lookout,but it won't notice a foe coming from behind.

pokemon.name: Watchog
pokemon.pokedex: When they see an enemy,their tails stand high,and they spit the seeds of berries stored in their cheek pouches.

pokemon.name: Lillipup
pokemon.pokedex: This Pokémon is courageous but also cautious. It uses the soft fur covering its face to collect information about its surroundings.

pokemon.name: Herdier
pokemon.pokedex: Herdier is a very smart and friendly Pokémon. So much so that there's a theory that Herdier was the first Pokémon to partner with people.

pokemon.name: Stoutland
pokemon.pokedex: Stoutland is immensely proud of its impressive moustache. It's said that moustache length is what determines social standing among this species.

pokemon.name: Purrloin
pokemon.pokedex: Opponents that get drawn in by its adorable behavior come away with stinging scratches from its claws and stinging pride from its laughter.

pokemon.name: Liepard
pokemon.pokedex: This stealthy Pokémon sneaks up behind prey without making any sound at all. It competes with Thievul for territory.

pokemon.name: Pansage
pokemon.pokedex: It's good at finding berries and gathers them from all over. It's kind enough to share them with friends.

pokemon.name: Simisage
pokemon.pokedex: Ill tempered,it fights by swinging its barbed tail around wildly. The leaf growing on its head is very bitter.

pokemon.name: Pansear
pokemon.pokedex: This Pokémon lives in caves in volcanoes. The fire within the tuft on its head can reach 600 degrees Fahrenheit.

pokemon.name: Simisear
