pokemon.pokedex: When it gets excited,embers rise from its head and tail and it gets hot. For some reason,it loves sweets.

pokemon.name: Panpour
pokemon.pokedex: The water stored inside the tuft on its head is full of nutrients. Plants that receive its water grow large.

pokemon.name: Simipour
pokemon.pokedex: It prefers places with clean water. When its tuft runs low,it replenishes it by siphoning up water with its tail.

pokemon.name: Munna
pokemon.pokedex: It eats dreams and releases mist. The mist is pink when it's eating a good dream,and black when it's eating a nightmare.

pokemon.name: Musharna
pokemon.pokedex: It drowses and dreams all the time. It's best to leave it be if it's just woken up,as it's a terrible grump when freshly roused from sleep.

pokemon.name: Pidove
pokemon.pokedex: It snobs other Pokemon,even shoving them aside when there's food nearby. Due to its small size,most of the time it's sent running with its tail between its legs.

pokemon.name: Tranquill
pokemon.pokedex: Adored by old ladies,they are often found in videos online due to their grumpy nature. Seeing one in the wild is a rare sight.

pokemon.name: Unfezant
pokemon.pokedex: Narcissistic like little else,they often annoy other Pokemon and end up in fights. Unlike Pidove's,the powerful legs of an Unfezant are a fierce and effective weapon.

pokemon.name: Blitzle
pokemon.pokedex: Its mane shines when it discharges electricity. They use the frequency and rhythm of these flashes to communicate.

pokemon.name: Zebstrika
pokemon.pokedex: They have lightning-like movements. When Zebstrika run at full speed,the sound of thunder reverberates.

pokemon.name: Roggenrola
pokemon.pokedex: When it detects a noise,it starts to move. The energy core inside it makes this Pokémon slightly warm to the touch.

pokemon.name: Boldore
pokemon.pokedex: It relies on sound in order to monitor what's in its vicinity. When angered,it will attack without ever changing the direction it's facing.

pokemon.name: Gigalith
pokemon.pokedex: Although its energy blasts can blow away a dump truck. They have a limitation,they can only be fired when the sun is out.

pokemon.name: Woobat
pokemon.pokedex: While inside a cave,if you look up and see lots of heart-shaped marks lining the walls,it's evidence that Woobat live there.

pokemon.name: Swoobat
pokemon.pokedex: The auspicious shape of this Pokémon's nose apparently led some regions to consider Swoobat a symbol of good luck.

pokemon.name: Drilbur
pokemon.pokedex: It's a digger,using its claws to burrow through the ground. It causes damage to vegetable crops,so many farmers have little love for it.

pokemon.name: Excadrill
pokemon.pokedex: It's not uncommon for tunnels that appear to have formed naturally to actually be a result of Excadrill's rampant digging.

pokemon.name: Audino
pokemon.pokedex: Audino's sense of hearing is superb. Not even a pebble rolling along over a mile away will escape Audino's ears.

pokemon.name: Timburr
pokemon.pokedex: It loves helping out with construction projects. It loves it so much that if rain causes work to halt,it swings its log around and throws a tantrum.

pokemon.name: Gurdurr
pokemon.pokedex: Gurdurr excels at demolition. Construction is not its forte. In any case,there's skill in the way this Pokémon wields its metal beam.

pokemon.name: Conkeldurr
pokemon.pokedex: Concrete mixed by Conkeldurr is much more durable than normal concrete,even when the compositions of the two materials are the same.

pokemon.name: Tympole
pokemon.pokedex: It uses sound waves to communicate with others of its kind. People and other Pokémon species can't hear its cries of warning.

pokemon.name: Palpitoad
pokemon.pokedex: On occasion,their cries are sublimely pleasing to the ear. Palpitoad with larger lumps on their bodies can sing with a wider range of sounds.

pokemon.name: Seismitoad
pokemon.pokedex: The vibrating of the bumps all over its body causes earthquake-like tremors. Seismitoad and Croagunk are similar species.

pokemon.name: Throh
pokemon.pokedex: It performs throwing moves with first-rate skill. Over the course of many battles,Throh's belt grows darker as it absorbs its wearer's sweat.

pokemon.name: Sawk
pokemon.pokedex: If you see a Sawk training in the mountains in its single-minded pursuit of strength,it's best to quietly pass by.

pokemon.name: Sewaddle
pokemon.pokedex: Since this Pokémon makes its own clothes out of leaves,it is a popular mascot for fashion designers.

pokemon.name: Swadloon
pokemon.pokedex: It protects itself from the cold by wrapping up in leaves. It stays on the move,eating leaves in forests.

pokemon.name: Leavanny
pokemon.pokedex: It keeps its eggs warm with heat from fermenting leaves. It also uses leaves to make warm wrappings for Sewaddle.

pokemon.name: Venipede
pokemon.pokedex: Known to be territorial,they gnaw at mineral deposits and use them as fuel for their electricity.

pokemon.name: Whirlipede
pokemon.pokedex: Whirlipedes are often domesticated,as their excess amount of electricity through evolution allows them to power generators without strain.

pokemon.name: Scolipede
pokemon.pokedex: Seemingly coming from outside of the region,they host the capacity to power entire cities with the electricity circuiting through their body.

pokemon.name: Cottonee
pokemon.pokedex: They go wherever the wind takes them. On rainy days,their bodies are heavier,so they take shelter beneath big trees.

pokemon.name: Whimsicott
pokemon.pokedex: Riding whirlwinds,they appear. These Pokémon sneak through gaps into houses and cause all sorts of mischief.

pokemon.name: Petilil
pokemon.pokedex: Petilil appears around sources of clean water. Boiling leaves from this Pokémon's head results in a liquid that's sometimes used as a bug repellent.

pokemon.name: Lilligant
pokemon.pokedex: It's believed that even first-rate gardeners have a hard time getting the flower on a Lilligant's head to bloom

pokemon.name: Basculin
pokemon.pokedex: Anglers love the fight this Pokémon puts up on the hook. And there are always more to catch. Many people release them into lakes illicitly.

pokemon.name: Sandile
pokemon.pokedex: Sandile is small,but its legs and lower body are powerful. Pushing snow aside as it goes,Sandile moves through the tundra as if it's swimming.

pokemon.name: Krokorok
pokemon.pokedex: Although this Pokémon has specialized eyes that allow it to see well in water,Krokorok aren't adept swimmers.

pokemon.name: Krookodile
pokemon.pokedex: This Pokemon is known as the Bully of the Tundra. Krookodile's mighty jaws can bite through permafrost with ease.

pokemon.name: Darumaka
pokemon.pokedex: It derives its power from fire burning inside its body. If the fire dwindles,this Pokémon will immediately fall asleep.

pokemon.name: Darmanitan
pokemon.pokedex: This Pokémon's power level rises along with the temperature of its fire,which can reach 2,500 degrees Fahrenheit.

pokemon.name: Maractus
pokemon.pokedex: With noises that could be mistaken for the rattles of maracas,it creates an upbeat rhythm,startling bird Pokémon and making them fly off in a hurry.

pokemon.name: Dwebble
pokemon.pokedex: The plant on top of its back secretes a sticky substance similar to glue. Sometimes,Dwebble will have items attached to it,like Heart Scales.

pokemon.name: Crustle
pokemon.pokedex: This highly territorial Pokémon prefers dry climates. It won't come out of its boulder on rainy days.

pokemon.name: Scraggy
pokemon.pokedex: If it locks eyes with you,watch out! Nothing and no one is safe from the reckless headbutts of this troublesome Pokémon.

pokemon.name: Scrafty
pokemon.pokedex: While mostly known for having the temperament of an aggressive ruffian,this Pokémon takes very good care of its family,friends,and territory.

pokemon.name: Sigilyph
pokemon.pokedex: Psychic power allows these Pokémon to fly. Some say they were the guardians of an ancient city. Others say they were the guardians' emissaries.

pokemon.name: Yamask
pokemon.pokedex: The spirit of a person from a bygone age became this Pokémon. It rambles through ruins,searching for someone who knows its face.

pokemon.name: Cofagrigus
pokemon.pokedex: There are many depictions of Cofagrigus decorating ancient tombs. They're symbols of the wealth that kings of bygone eras had.

pokemon.name: Tirtouga
pokemon.pokedex: This Pokémon inhabited ancient seas. Although it can only crawl,it still comes up onto land in search of prey.

pokemon.name: Carracosta
pokemon.pokedex: Carracosta completely devours its prey,bones,shells,and all. Because of this,Carracosta's own shell grows thick and sturdy.

pokemon.name: Archen
pokemon.pokedex: While its underdeveloped wings prevent it from flying,it can jump up to 30 feet in the air.

pokemon.name: Archeops
pokemon.pokedex: Scientists believe this was the true form of Archeops,millions of years ago. Its legs are powerful enough to overturn a truck,but it is only able to glide small distances.

pokemon.name: Trubbish
pokemon.pokedex: Its favorite places are unsanitary ones. If you leave trash lying around,you could even find one of these Pokémon living in your room.

pokemon.name: Garbodor
pokemon.pokedex: This Pokémon eats trash,which turns into poison inside its body. The main component of the poison depends on what sort of trash was eaten.

pokemon.name: Zorua
pokemon.pokedex: It attracts lost humans and Pokemon with mirages,which it then rescues from the unforgiving desert heat. Travelers dispersed in the dunes are usually found near an oasis.

pokemon.name: Zoroark
pokemon.pokedex: It attracts lost humans and Pokemon with mirages,which it then rescues from the unforgiving desert heat. Travelers dispersed in the dunes are usually found near an oasis.

pokemon.name: Minccino
pokemon.pokedex: Old ladies adore this Pokemon,even if it tends to steal jewelry while no one's looking. Everyone finds it adorable though.

pokemon.name: Cinccino
pokemon.pokedex: The patterns of Cinccino help it to mimethize in the wild,while it uses its electric powers to steal all sorts of metallic treasure.

pokemon.name: Gothita
pokemon.pokedex: Even when nobody seems to be around,Gothita can still be heard making a muted cry. Many believe it's speaking to something only it can see.

pokemon.name: Gothorita
pokemon.pokedex: On nights when the stars shine,this Pokémon's psychic power is at its strongest. It's unknown just what link Gothorita has to the greater universe.

pokemon.name: Gothitelle
pokemon.pokedex: It has tremendous psychic power,but it dislikes conflict. It's also able to predict the future based on the movement of the stars.

pokemon.name: Solosis
pokemon.pokedex: Its body is encapsulated in liquid,but if it takes a heavy blow,the liquid will leak out.

pokemon.name: Duosion
pokemon.pokedex: Its body is encapsulated in liquid,but if it takes a heavy blow,the liquid will leak out.

pokemon.name: Reuniclus
pokemon.pokedex: Reuniclus might be one of the first complex lifeforms that appeared on the planet,as the water coating it produces easily survives even the strongest pressure underwater.

pokemon.name: Ducklett
pokemon.pokedex: This Pokemon can only make friends with others they deem as less beautiful then them. It has a deep hatred for Pokemon more beautiful than itself.

pokemon.name: Swanna
pokemon.pokedex: It hunts down butterfly-like Pokemon and takes their wings to add to its own. It's rumored this Pokemon caused the mass reduction in Ayrei's Vivillon population.

pokemon.name: Vanillite
pokemon.pokedex: Unable to survive in cold areas,it makes itself comfortable by breathing out air to cause sandstorms. It burrows into the sand to sleep.

pokemon.name: Vanillish
pokemon.pokedex: It blasts enemies with hot air reaching 200 degrees Fahrenheit,burning them. But it spares their lives afterwards. It's a kind PokÃ©mon.

pokemon.name: Vanilluxe
pokemon.pokedex: Its outer shell is as hot as the inside of an active volcano. It obliviously burns everything in its vicinity to a crisp,be it friend or foe.

pokemon.name: Deerling
pokemon.pokedex: At night,their horns glow with light,allowing them to communicate with other members of the herd. They are believed to have near-human intelligence.

pokemon.name: Sawsbuck
pokemon.pokedex: These Sawsbuck grow more powerful the more knowledge they acquire,signified by the glow of their antlers. The ones with the most luminous antlers are the leaders of the herd.

pokemon.name: Emolga
pokemon.pokedex: This Pokémon absolutely loves sweet berries. Sometimes it stuffs its cheeks full of so much food that it can't fly properly.

pokemon.name: Karrablast
pokemon.pokedex: For some reason they evolve when they receive electrical energy while they are attacking Shelmet.

pokemon.name: Escavalier
pokemon.pokedex: It charges its enemies,lances at the ready. An image of one of its duels is captured in a famous painting of Escavalier clashing with Sirfetch'd.

pokemon.name: Foongus
pokemon.pokedex: The spores released from this Pokémon's hands are highly poisonous,but when thoroughly dried,the spores can be used as stomach medicine.

pokemon.name: Amoonguss
pokemon.pokedex: This Pokémon puffs poisonous spores at its foes. If the spores aren't washed off quickly,they'll grow into mushrooms wherever they land.

pokemon.name: Frillish
pokemon.pokedex: It envelops its prey in its veillike arms and draws it down to the deeps,five miles below the ocean's surface.

pokemon.name: Jellicent
pokemon.pokedex: Whenever a full moon hangs in the night sky,schools of Jellicent gather near the surface of the sea,waiting for their prey to appear.

pokemon.name: Alomomola
pokemon.pokedex: It gently holds injured and weak Pokémon in its fins. Its special membrane heals their wounds.

pokemon.name: Joltik
pokemon.pokedex: Joltik can be found clinging to other Pokémon. It's soaking up static electricity because it can't produce a charge on its own.

pokemon.name: Galvantula
pokemon.pokedex: It launches electrified fur from its abdomen as its means of attack. Opponents hit by the fur could be in for three full days and nights of paralysis.

pokemon.name: Ferroseed
pokemon.pokedex: Mossy caves are their preferred dwellings. Enzymes contained in mosses help Ferroseed's spikes grow big and strong.

pokemon.name: Ferrothorn
pokemon.pokedex: This Pokémon scrapes its spikes across rocks,and then uses the tips of its feelers to absorb the nutrients it finds within the stone.

pokemon.name: Klink
pokemon.pokedex: The two minigears that compose this Pokémon are closer than twins. They mesh well only with each other.

pokemon.name: Klang
pokemon.pokedex: When Klang goes all out,the minigear links up perfectly with the outer part of the big gear,and this Pokémon's rotation speed increases sharply.

pokemon.name: Klinklang
pokemon.pokedex: From its spikes,it launches powerful blasts of electricity. Its red core contains an enormous amount of energy.

pokemon.name: Tynamo
pokemon.pokedex: One alone can emit only a trickle of electricity,so a group of them gathers to unleash a powerful electric shock.

pokemon.name: Eelektrik
pokemon.pokedex: These Pokémon have a big appetite. When they spot their prey,they attack it and paralyze it with electricity.

pokemon.name: Eelektross
pokemon.pokedex: They crawl out of the ocean using their arms. They will attack prey on shore and immediately drag it into the ocean.

pokemon.name: Elgyem
pokemon.pokedex: If this Pokémon stands near a TV,strange scenery will appear on the screen. That scenery is said to be from its home.

pokemon.name: Beheeyem
pokemon.pokedex: Sometimes found drifting above wheat fields,this Pokémon can control the memories of its opponents.

pokemon.name: Litwick
pokemon.pokedex: The flame on its head keeps its body slightly warm. This Pokémon takes lost children by the hand to guide them to the spirit world.

pokemon.name: Lampent
pokemon.pokedex: It lurks in cities,pretending to be a lamp. Once it finds someone whose death is near,it will trail quietly after them.

pokemon.name: Chandelure
pokemon.pokedex: This Pokémon haunts dilapidated mansions. It sways its arms to hypnotize opponents with the ominous dancing of its flames.

pokemon.name: Axew
pokemon.pokedex: They subsist on ruby gemstones found deep within the region,it's theorized that these Pokemon have been adapted to this diet over the course of many years.

pokemon.name: Fraxure
pokemon.pokedex: They are very protective of their peers,and in equal measures are they territorial. Their ruby tusks can channel energy through stones to amplify their strength.

pokemon.name: Haxorus
pokemon.pokedex: They have become very rare due to poachers seeking their tusks. As such,the remaining Haxorus are ruthless,and known to collapse entire mountains to protect their kin.

pokemon.name: Cubchoo
pokemon.pokedex: When this Pokémon is in good health,its snot becomes thicker and stickier. It will smear its snot on anyone it doesn't like.

pokemon.name: Beartic
pokemon.pokedex: It swims energetically through frigid seas. When it gets tired,it freezes the seawater with its breath so it can rest on the ice.

pokemon.name: Cryogonal
pokemon.pokedex: When the weather gets hot,these Pokémon turn into water vapor. Cryogonal are almost never seen during summer.

pokemon.name: Shelmet
pokemon.pokedex: When attacked,it tightly shuts the lid of its shell. This reaction fails to protect it from Karrablast,however,because they can still get into the shell.

pokemon.name: Accelgor
pokemon.pokedex: It moves with blinding speed and lobs poison at foes. Featuring Accelgor as a main character is a surefire way to make a movie or comic popular.

pokemon.name: Stunfisk
pokemon.pokedex: For some reason,this Pokémon smiles slightly when it emits a strong electric current from the yellow markings on its body.

pokemon.name: Mienfoo
pokemon.pokedex: Though small,Mienfoo's temperament is fierce. Any creature that approaches Mienfoo carelessly will be greeted with a flurry of graceful attacks.

pokemon.name: Mienshao
pokemon.pokedex: When Mienshao comes across a truly challenging opponent,it will lighten itself by biting off the fur on its arms.

pokemon.name: Druddigon
pokemon.pokedex: Devious and opportunistic,it flies through Cyberspace in search of vulnerable files to infect. Unreliable sources say that they were made by a group of hackers that opposed the war.

pokemon.name: Golett
pokemon.pokedex: This Pokémon was created from clay. It received orders from its master many thousands of years ago,and it still follows those orders to this day.

pokemon.name: Golurk
pokemon.pokedex: There's a theory that inside Golurk is a perpetual motion machine that produces limitless energy,but this belief hasn't been proven.

pokemon.name: Pawniard
pokemon.pokedex: It uses river stones to maintain the cutting edges of the blades covering its body. These sharpened blades allow it to bring down opponents.

pokemon.name: Bisharp
pokemon.pokedex: It's accompanied by a large retinue of Pawniard. Bisharp keeps a keen eye on its minions,ensuring none of them even think of double-crossing it.

pokemon.name: Bouffalant
pokemon.pokedex: These Pokémon live in herds of about 20 individuals. Bouffalant that betray the herd will lose the hair on their heads for some reason.

pokemon.name: Rufflet
pokemon.pokedex: If it spies a strong Pokémon,Rufflet can't resist challenging it to a battle. But if Rufflet loses,it starts bawling.

pokemon.name: Braviary
pokemon.pokedex: Because this Pokémon is hotheaded and belligerent,it's Corviknight that's taken the role of transportation in Galar.

pokemon.name: Vullaby
pokemon.pokedex: Vullaby grow quickly. Bones that have gotten too small for older Vullaby to wear often get passed down to younger ones in the nest.

pokemon.name: Mandibuzz
pokemon.pokedex: They adorn themselves with bones. There seem to be fashion trends among them,as different bones come into and fall out of popularity.

pokemon.name: Heatmor
pokemon.pokedex: There's a hole in its tail that allows it to draw in the air it needs to keep its fire burning. If the hole gets blocked,this Pokémon will fall ill.

pokemon.name: Durant
pokemon.pokedex: With their large mandibles,these Pokémon can crunch their way through rock. They work together to protect their eggs from Sandaconda.

pokemon.name: Deino
pokemon.pokedex: When it encounters something,its first urge is usually to bite it. If it likes what it tastes,it will commit the associated scent to memory.

pokemon.name: Zweilous
pokemon.pokedex: Their two heads will fight each other over a single piece of food. Zweilous are covered in scars even without battling others.

pokemon.name: Hydreigon
pokemon.pokedex: It brings famine wherever it goes,as its insatiable hunger cannot be contained. Hydreigon usage is heavily regulated,as most trainers cannot quell them.

pokemon.name: Larvesta
pokemon.pokedex: Larvesta's body is warm all over. It spouts fire from the tips of its horns to intimidate predators and scare prey.

pokemon.name: Volcarona
pokemon.pokedex: Volcarona scatters burning scales. Some say it does this to start fires. Others say it's trying to rescue those that suffer in the cold.

pokemon.name: Cobalion
pokemon.pokedex: It has a body and heart of steel. It worked with its allies to punish people when they hurt Pokémon.

pokemon.name: Terrakion
pokemon.pokedex: Spoken of in legend,this Pokémon used its phenomenal power to destroy a castle in its effort to protect Pokémon.

pokemon.name: Virizion
pokemon.pokedex: Legends say this Pokémon confounded opponents with its swift movements.

pokemon.name: Tornadus
pokemon.pokedex: Tornadus expels massive energy from its tail,causing severe storms. Its power is great enough to blow houses away.

pokemon.name: Thundurus
pokemon.pokedex: The spikes on its tail discharge immense bolts of lightning. It flies around the Unova region firing off lightning bolts.

pokemon.name: Reshiram
pokemon.pokedex: When Reshiram's tail flares,the heat energy moves the atmosphere and changes the world's weather.

pokemon.name: Zekrom
pokemon.pokedex: Concealing itself in lightning clouds,it flies throughout the Unova region. It creates electricity in its tail.

pokemon.name: Landorus
pokemon.pokedex: Lands visited by Landorus grant such bountiful crops that it has been hailed as "The Guardian of the Fields."

pokemon.name: Kyurem
pokemon.pokedex: It generates a powerful,freezing energy inside itself,but its body became frozen when the energy leaked out.

pokemon.name: Keldeo
pokemon.pokedex: When it is resolute,its body fills with power and it becomes swifter. Its jumps are then too fast to follow.

pokemon.name: Meloetta
pokemon.pokedex: Its melodies are sung with a special vocalization method that can control the feelings of those who hear it.

pokemon.name: Genesect
pokemon.pokedex: This Pokémon existed 300 million years ago. Team Plasma altered it and attached a cannon to its back.

pokemon.name: Chespin
pokemon.pokedex: Such a thick shell of wood covers its head and back that even a direct hit from a truck wouldn't faze it.

pokemon.name: Quilladin
pokemon.pokedex: They strengthen their lower bodies by running into one another. They are very kind and won't start fights.

pokemon.name: Chesnaught
pokemon.pokedex: When it takes a defensive posture with its fists guarding its face,it could withstand a bomb blast.

pokemon.name: Fennekin
pokemon.pokedex: This Pokemon is only seen near secluded icy lakes. They only emerge to drink from the springs when they are alone.

pokemon.name: Braixen
pokemon.pokedex: The budding voices of these foxes produce may produce beautiful auroras during the night. However,they are quick to stop and run away should they be discovered.

pokemon.name: Delphox
pokemon.pokedex: "Travelers may be able to witness the songs of these foxes during an aurora. However,their voices also enhance the ice they use to chase off unwanted company."

pokemon.name: Froakie
pokemon.pokedex: Is is able to stay completely still for hours at a time,but when one draws near it,it will suddenly awaken and escape to below the water's surface.

pokemon.name: Frogadier
pokemon.pokedex: Sightings of this Pokemon have only been reported relatively recently. It was once thought that wild Froakie directly evolved to Greninja,and that trainer intervention delayed this evolution.

pokemon.name: Greninja
pokemon.pokedex: Completely in tune with nature,it is a symbol of peace and prosperity. A Greninja is the hallmark of a healthy and flourishing fresh water ecosystem.

pokemon.name: Bunnelby
pokemon.pokedex: It's very sensitive to danger. The sound of Corviknight's flapping will have Bunnelby digging a hole to hide underground in moments.

pokemon.name: Diggersby
pokemon.pokedex: The fur on its belly retains heat exceptionally well. People used to make heavy winter clothing from fur shed by this Pokémon.

pokemon.name: Fletchling
pokemon.pokedex: "The small ember that rests atop their head doesn't burn out even when doused in water. They will often stick their heads into the burrows of their prey to lure them out with the flames."

pokemon.name: Fletchinder
pokemon.pokedex: "Now able to fly for days at a time,Ayreian Fletchinders hunt diligently by the sea,picking off even the most agile swimmers thanks to its feathers not being hindered by water."

pokemon.name: Fleumflame
pokemon.pokedex: "Historically regarded as heralds or signs of rainfall to come in the wake of a drought,Fleumflames are often seen soaring across the ocean,where they can dive hundreds of meters beneath the surface to hunt prey that are drawn to their flame's light."

pokemon.name: Scatterbug
pokemon.pokedex: The powder that covers its body regulates its temperature,so it can live in any region or climate.

pokemon.name: Spewpa
pokemon.pokedex: The beaks of bird Pokémon can't begin to scratch its stalwart body. To defend itself,it spews powder.

pokemon.name: Vivillon

pokemon.pokedex: The patterns on this Pokémon's wings depend on the climate and topography of its habitat. It scatters colorful scales.

pokemon.name: Litleo
pokemon.pokedex: It can be found in greatly polluted areas. The fumes that emit from their mane can knock out a full-grown adult.

pokemon.name: Pyroar
pokemon.pokedex: Adapted to the polluted grounds that have become its territory,it preys upon the smaller Pokémon in the urban landscape and defends its territory viciously from humankind.

pokemon.name: Flabébé
pokemon.pokedex: When it finds a flower it likes,it dwells on that flower its whole life long. It floats in the wind's embrace with an untroubled heart.

pokemon.name: Floette
pokemon.pokedex: When the flowers of a well-tended flower bed bloom,it appears and celebrates with an elegant dance.

pokemon.name: Florges
pokemon.pokedex: In times long past,governors of castles would invite Florges to create flower gardens to embellish the castle domains.

pokemon.name: Skiddo
pokemon.pokedex: Amicable and excitable beings,Skiddo will often frolic along the shorelines with people and Pokemon alike.

pokemon.name: Gogoat
pokemon.pokedex: Living on the oceans surface,they race along the waves and are revered by sailors for their ability to calm the sea itself.

pokemon.name: Pancham
pokemon.pokedex: Wanting to make sure it's taken seriously,Pancham's always giving others a glare. But if it's not focusing,it ends up smiling.

pokemon.name: Pangoro
pokemon.pokedex: Angrier than a raging inferno,it pummels opponents with a fiery might. The fire emanating from its body is hot enough to melt the metal of a jet plane.

pokemon.name: Furfrou
pokemon.pokedex: Historically,in the Kalos region,these Pokémon were the designated guardians of the king.

pokemon.name: Espurr
pokemon.pokedex: There's enough psychic power in Espurr to send a wrestler flying,but because this power can't be controlled,Espurr finds it troublesome.

pokemon.name: Meowstic
pokemon.pokedex: Revealing the eyelike patterns on the insides of its ears will unleash its psychic powers. It normally keeps the patterns hidden,however.

pokemon.name: Honedge
pokemon.pokedex: Honedge's soul once belonged to a person who was killed a long time ago by the sword that makes up Honedge's body.

pokemon.name: Doublade
pokemon.pokedex: The two swords employ a strategy of rapidly alternating between offense and defense to bring down their prey.

pokemon.name: Aegislash
pokemon.pokedex: Its potent spectral powers allow it to manipulate others. It once used its powers to force people and Pokémon to build a kingdom to its liking.

pokemon.name: Spritzee
pokemon.pokedex: A scent pouch within this Pokémon's body allows it to create various scents. A change in its diet will alter the fragrance it produces.

pokemon.name: Aromatisse
pokemon.pokedex: The scent that constantly emits from its fur is so powerful that this Pokémon's companions will eventually lose their sense of smell.

pokemon.name: Swirlix
pokemon.pokedex: The sweet smell of cotton candy perfumes Swirlix's fluffy fur. This Pokémon spits out sticky string to tangle up its enemies.

pokemon.name: Slurpuff
pokemon.pokedex: By taking in a person's scent,it can sniff out their mental and physical condition. It's hoped that this skill will have many medical applications.

pokemon.name: Inkay
pokemon.pokedex: It spins while making its luminescent spots flash. These spots allow it to communicate with others by using different patterns of light.

pokemon.name: Malamar
pokemon.pokedex: Gazing at its luminescent spots will quickly induce a hypnotic state,putting the observer under Malamar's control.

pokemon.name: Binacle
pokemon.pokedex: After two Binacle find a suitably sized rock,they adhere themselves to it and live together. They cooperate to gather food during high tide.

pokemon.name: Barbaracle
pokemon.pokedex: Having an eye on each palm allows it to keep watch in all directions. In a pinch,its limbs start to act on their own to ensure the enemy's defeat.

pokemon.name: Skrelp
pokemon.pokedex: It drifts in the ocean,blending in with floating seaweed. When other Pokémon come to feast on the seaweed,Skrelp feasts on them instead.

pokemon.name: Dragalge
pokemon.pokedex: Dragalge generates dragon energy by sticking the plume on its head out above the ocean's surface and bathing it in sunlight.

pokemon.name: Clauncher
pokemon.pokedex: By detonating gas that accumulates in its right claw,this Pokémon launches water like a bullet. This is how Clauncher defeats its enemies.

pokemon.name: Clawitzer
pokemon.pokedex: Clawitzer's right arm is a cannon that launches projectiles made of seawater. Shots from a Clawitzer's cannon arm can sink a tanker.

pokemon.name: Helioptile
pokemon.pokedex: Secreting a thick inky substance from their scales since birth,helioptile leave trails of it wherever they go.

pokemon.name: Heliolisk
pokemon.pokedex: They use their ink to paint crude symbols on their paper like frills,expanding them to communicate to others.

pokemon.name: Tyrunt
pokemon.pokedex: This is an ancient Pokémon. It has a violent disposition,and it uses its hefty jaws to tear everything apart.

pokemon.name: Tyrantrum
pokemon.pokedex: After being buried for 100,000,000 years in a volcano,this Pokémon has been altered by the heat. It has the presence of a king,vicious but magnificent.

pokemon.name: Amaura
pokemon.pokedex: This Pokémon was successfully restored from a fossil. In the past,it lived with others of its kind in cold lands where there were fewer predators.

pokemon.name: Aurorus
pokemon.pokedex: Aurorus was restored from a fossil. It's said that when this Pokémon howls,auroras appear in the night sky.

pokemon.name: Sylveon
pokemon.pokedex: There's a Galarian fairy tale that describes a beautiful Sylveon vanquishing a dreadful dragon Pokémon.

pokemon.name: Hawlucha
pokemon.pokedex: It always strikes a pose before going for its finishing move. Sometimes opponents take advantage of that time to counterattack.

pokemon.name: Dedenne
pokemon.pokedex: Since Dedenne can't generate much electricity on its own,it steals electricity from outlets or other electric Pokémon.

pokemon.name: Carbink
pokemon.pokedex: The bands of iron spinning around it's core protect it from almost every kind of attack

pokemon.name: Goomy
pokemon.pokedex: Their horns are powerful sensors. As soon as Goomy pick up any sign of enemies,they go into hiding. This is how they've survived.

pokemon.name: Sliggoo
pokemon.pokedex: Although this Pokémon isn't very strong,its body is coated in a caustic slime that can melt through anything,so predators steer clear of it.

pokemon.name: Goodra
pokemon.pokedex: Sometimes it misunderstands instructions and appears dazed or bewildered. Many Trainers don't mind,finding this behavior to be adorable.

pokemon.name: Klefki
pokemon.pokedex: Radiating with electricity,it was commonly used to access electronically locked facilities.

pokemon.name: Phantump
pokemon.pokedex: After a lost child perished in the forest,their spirit possessed a tree stump,causing the spirit's rebirth as this Pokémon.

pokemon.name: Trevenant
pokemon.pokedex: A collection of lost spirits,with the sole purpose of defending wildlife from those who seek to destroy it.

pokemon.name: Pumpkaboo
pokemon.pokedex: When taking spirits to the afterlife,small Pumpkaboo prefer the spirits of children to those of adults.

pokemon.name: Gourgeist
pokemon.pokedex: Soft cries emanate from its body in the dead of night. The sounds are said to be the wails of spirits who are resting in the afterlife.

pokemon.name: Bergmite
pokemon.pokedex: They chill the air around them to -150 degrees Fahrenheit,freezing the water in the air into ice that they use as armor.

pokemon.name: Avalugg
pokemon.pokedex: As Avalugg moves about during the day,the cracks in its body deepen. The Pokémon's body returns to a pristine state overnight.

pokemon.name: Noibat
pokemon.pokedex: It is blind,and it spreads bright scales while fluttering about that keep predators from attacking it.

pokemon.name: Noivern
pokemon.pokedex: While it may look intimidating,it has a gentle and caring disposition. That said,it will shoot down anyone threatening its protégé with beams of light.

pokemon.name: Xerneas
pokemon.pokedex: When the horns on its head shine in seven colors,it is said to be sharing everlasting life.

pokemon.name: Yveltal
pokemon.pokedex: When its life comes to an end,it absorbs the life energy of every living thing and turns into a cocoon once more.

pokemon.name: Zygarde
pokemon.pokedex: Some say it can change to an even more powerful form when battling those who threaten the ecosystem.

pokemon.name: Diancie
pokemon.pokedex: It can instantly create many diamonds by compressing the carbon in the air between its hands.

pokemon.name: Hoopa
pokemon.pokedex: It gathers things it likes and passes them through its loop to teleport them to a secret place.

pokemon.name: Volcanion
pokemon.pokedex: It expels its internal steam from the arms on its back. It has enough power to blow away a mountain.

pokemon.name: Rowlet
pokemon.pokedex: It sends its feathers,which are as sharp as blades,flying in attack. Its legs are strong,so its kicks are also formidable.

pokemon.name: Dartrix
pokemon.pokedex: This narcissistic Pokémon is a clean freak. If you don't groom it diligently,it will stop listening to you.

pokemon.name: Decidueye
pokemon.pokedex: It nocks its arrow quills and shoots them at opponents. When it simply can't afford to miss,it tugs the vine on its head to improve its focus.

pokemon.name: Litten
pokemon.pokedex: If you try too hard to get close to it,it won't open up to you. Even if you do grow close,giving it too much affection is still a no-no.

pokemon.name: Torracat
pokemon.pokedex: It can act spoiled if it grows close to its Trainer. A powerful Pokémon,its sharp claws can leave its Trainer's whole body covered in scratches.

pokemon.name: Incineroar
pokemon.pokedex: Although it's rough mannered and egotistical,it finds beating down unworthy opponents boring. It gets motivated for stronger opponents.

pokemon.name: Popplio
pokemon.pokedex: The balloons it inflates with its nose grow larger and larger as it practices day by day.

pokemon.name: Brionne
pokemon.pokedex: It gets excited when it sees a dance it doesn't know. This hard worker practices diligently until it can learn that dance.

pokemon.name: Primarina
pokemon.pokedex: To Primarina,every battle is a stage. It takes down its prey with beautiful singing and dancing.

pokemon.name: Pikipek
pokemon.pokedex: It pecks at trees with its hard beak. You can get some idea of its mood or condition from the rhythm of its pecking.

pokemon.name: Trumbeak
pokemon.pokedex: It can bend the tip of its beak to produce over a hundred different cries at will.

pokemon.name: Toucannon
pokemon.pokedex: They smack beaks with others of their kind to communicate. The strength and number of hits tell each other how they feel.

pokemon.name: Yungoos
pokemon.pokedex: An abrasive Pokemon that will do anything to get its way. Many children try to keep one as a pet,much to their parents' dismay.

pokemon.name: Gumshoos
pokemon.pokedex: This Pokemon finds joy in hurting and taking from others. Despite this fact,it seems to be good with children.

pokemon.name: Grubbin
pokemon.pokedex: Its natural enemies,like Rookidee,may flee rather than risk getting caught in its large mandibles that can snap thick tree branches.

pokemon.name: Charjabug
pokemon.pokedex: While its durable shell protects it from attacks,Charjabug strikes at enemies with jolts of electricity discharged from the tips of its jaws.

pokemon.name: Vikavolt
pokemon.pokedex: It builds up electricity in its abdomen,focuses it through its jaws,and then fires the electricity off in concentrated beams.

pokemon.name: Crabrawler
pokemon.pokedex: Its hard pincers are well suited to both offense and defense. Fights between two Crabrawler are like boxing matches.

pokemon.name: Crabominable
pokemon.pokedex: It stores coldness in its pincers and pummels its foes. It can even smash thick walls of ice to bits!

pokemon.name: Oricorio
pokemon.pokedex: It wins the hearts of its enemies with its passionate dancing and then uses the opening it creates to burn them up with blazing flames.

pokemon.name: Cutiefly
pokemon.pokedex: It propels itself forward by combusting its sweat,which creates a small explosion similar to gunpowder.

pokemon.name: Ribombee
pokemon.pokedex: During the New Year night,multiple Ribombee can be seen fluttering in the sky,creating eye-striking explosions via their peculiar powder.

pokemon.name: Rockruff
pokemon.pokedex: This Pokémon intimidates opponents by striking the ground with the rocks on its neck. The moment an opponent flinches,Rockruff attacks.

pokemon.name: Lycanroc
pokemon.pokedex: With swift movements,this Pokémon gradually backs its prey into a corner. Lycanroc's fangs are always aimed toward opponents' weak spots.

pokemon.name: Wishiwashi
pokemon.pokedex: Individually,they're incredibly weak. It's by gathering up into schools that they're able to confront opponents.

pokemon.name: Mareanie
pokemon.pokedex: The first symptom of its sting is numbness. The next is an itching sensation so intense that it's impossible to resist the urge to claw at your skin.

pokemon.name: Toxapex
pokemon.pokedex: Within the poison sac in its body is a poison so toxic that Pokémon as large as Wailord will still be suffering three days after it first takes effect.

pokemon.name: Mudbray
pokemon.pokedex: It eats dirt to create mud and smears this mud all over its feet,giving them the grip needed to walk on rough terrain without slipping.

pokemon.name: Mudsdale
pokemon.pokedex: Mud that hardens around a Mudsdale's legs sets harder than stone. It's so hard that it allows this Pokémon to scrap a truck with a single kick.

pokemon.name: Dewpider
pokemon.pokedex: It forms a water bubble at the rear of its body and then covers its head with it. Meeting another Dewpider means comparing water-bubble sizes.

pokemon.name: Araquanid
pokemon.pokedex: It launches water bubbles with its legs,drowning prey within the bubbles. This Pokémon can then take its time to savor its meal.

pokemon.name: Fomantis
pokemon.pokedex: When bathed in sunlight,this Pokémon emits a pleasantly sweet scent,which causes bug Pokémon to gather around it.

pokemon.name: Lurantis
pokemon.pokedex: The petals on this Pokémon's arms are thin and super sharp,and they can fire laser beams if Lurantis gathers light first.

pokemon.name: Morelull
pokemon.pokedex: Morelull live in forests that stay dark even during the day. They scatter flickering spores that put enemies to sleep.

pokemon.name: Shiinotic
pokemon.pokedex: Its flickering spores lure in prey and put them to sleep. Once this Pokémon has its prey snoozing,it drains their vitality with its fingertips.

pokemon.name: Salandit
pokemon.pokedex: Its venom sacs produce a fluid that this Pokémon then heats up with the flame in its tail. This process creates Salandit's poisonous gas.

pokemon.name: Salazzle
pokemon.pokedex: The winner of competitions between Salazzle is decided by which one has the most male Salandit with it.

pokemon.name: Stufful
pokemon.pokedex: The way it protects itself by flailing its arms may be an adorable sight,but stay well away. This is flailing that can snap thick tree trunks.

pokemon.name: Bewear
pokemon.pokedex: Once it accepts you as a friend,it tries to show its affection with a hug. Letting it do that is dangerous. It could easily shatter your bones.

pokemon.name: Bounsweet
pokemon.pokedex: When under attack,it secretes a sweet and delicious sweat. The scent only calls more enemies to it.

pokemon.name: Steenee
pokemon.pokedex: Any Corvisquire that pecks at this Pokémon will be greeted with a smack from its sepals followed by a sharp kick.

pokemon.name: Tsareena
pokemon.pokedex: A kick from the hardened tips of this Pokémon's legs leaves a wound in the opponent's body and soul that will never heal.

pokemon.name: Comfey
pokemon.pokedex: Comfey picks flowers with its vine and decorates itself with them. For some reason,flowers won't wither once they're attached to a Comfey.

pokemon.name: Oranguru
pokemon.pokedex: It knows the forest inside and out. If it comes across a wounded Pokémon,Oranguru will gather medicinal herbs to treat it.

pokemon.name: Passimian
pokemon.pokedex: Passimian live in groups of about 20,with each member performing an assigned role. Through cooperation,the group survives.

pokemon.name: Wimpod
pokemon.pokedex: It's nature's cleaner. It eats anything and everything,including garbage and rotten things. The ground near its nest is always clean.

pokemon.name: Golisopod
pokemon.pokedex: It will do anything to win,taking advantage of every opening and finishing opponents off with the small claws on its front legs.

pokemon.name: Sandygast
pokemon.pokedex: Sandygast mainly inhabits beaches. It takes control of anyone who puts their hand into its mouth,forcing them to make its body bigger.

pokemon.name: Palossand
pokemon.pokedex: Palossand is known as the Beach Nightmare. It pulls its prey down into the sand by controlling the sand itself,and then it sucks out their souls.

pokemon.name: Pyukumuku
pokemon.pokedex: It lives in warm,shallow waters. If it encounters a foe,it will spit out its internal organs as a means to punch them.

pokemon.name: Type: Null
pokemon.pokedex: Rumor has it that the theft of top-secret research notes led to a new instance of this Pokémon being created in the Galar region.

pokemon.name: Silvally
pokemon.pokedex: A solid bond of trust between this Pokémon and its Trainer awakened the strength hidden within Silvally. It can change its type at will.

pokemon.name: Minior
pokemon.pokedex: It lives in the ozone layer,where it becomes food for stronger Pokémon. When it tries to run away,it falls to the ground.

pokemon.name: Komala
pokemon.pokedex: It stays asleep from the moment it's born. When it falls into a deep sleep,it stops moving altogether.

pokemon.name: Turtonator
pokemon.pokedex: Eating sulfur in its volcanic habitat is what causes explosive compounds to develop in its shell. Its droppings are also dangerously explosive.

pokemon.name: Togedemaru
pokemon.pokedex: With the long hairs on its back,this Pokémon takes in electricity from other electric Pokémon. It stores what it absorbs in an electric sac.

pokemon.name: Mimikyu
pokemon.pokedex: Said to be a furious spirit that inhabited a popular doll. When said doll is damaged,the hatred of the specter takes form.

pokemon.name: Bruxish
pokemon.pokedex: It burrows beneath the sand,radiating psychic power from the protuberance on its head. It waits for prey as it surveys the area.

pokemon.name: Drampa
pokemon.pokedex: The mountains it calls home are nearly two miles in height. On rare occasions,it descends to play with the children living in the towns below.

pokemon.name: Dhelmise
pokemon.pokedex: After a piece of seaweed merged with debris from a sunken ship,it was reborn as this ghost Pokémon.

pokemon.name: Jangmo-o
pokemon.pokedex: Jangmo-o strikes its scales to communicate with others of its kind. Its scales are actually fur that's become as hard as metal.

pokemon.name: Hakamo-o
pokemon.pokedex: Before attacking its enemies,it clashes its scales together and roars. Its sharp claws shred the opposition.

pokemon.name: Kommo-o
pokemon.pokedex: It clatters its tail scales to unnerve opponents. This Pokémon will battle only those who stand steadfast in the face of this display.

pokemon.name: Tapu Koko
pokemon.pokedex: Although it's called a guardian deity,if a person or Pokémon puts it in a bad mood,it will become a malevolent deity and attack.

pokemon.name: Tapu Lele
pokemon.pokedex: It heals the wounds of people and Pokémon by sprinkling them with its sparkling scales. This guardian deity is worshiped on Akala.

pokemon.name: Tapu Bulu
pokemon.pokedex: Although it's called a guardian deity,it's violent enough to crush anyone it sees as an enemy.

pokemon.name: Tapu Fini
pokemon.pokedex: This guardian deity of Poni Island manipulates water. Because it lives deep within a thick fog,it came to be both feared and revered.

pokemon.name: Cosmog
pokemon.pokedex: Even though its helpless,gaseous body can be blown away by the slightest breeze,it doesn't seem to care.

pokemon.name: Cosmoem
pokemon.pokedex: The king who ruled Alola in times of antiquity called it the "cocoon of the stars" and built an altar to worship it.

pokemon.name: Solgaleo
pokemon.pokedex: Sometimes the result of its opening an Ultra Wormhole is that energy and life-forms from other worlds are called here to this world.

pokemon.name: Lunala
pokemon.pokedex: Records of it exist in writings from long,long ago,where it was known by the name "the beast that calls the moon."

pokemon.name: Nihilego
pokemon.pokedex: A life-form from another world,it was dubbed a UB and is thought to produce a strong neurotoxin.

pokemon.name: Buzzwole
pokemon.pokedex: Although it's alien to this world and a danger here,it's apparently a common organism in the world where it normally lives.

pokemon.name: Pheromosa
pokemon.pokedex: A life-form that lives in another world,its body is thin and supple,but it also possesses great power.

pokemon.name: Xurkitree
pokemon.pokedex: Although it's alien to this world and a danger here,it's apparently a common organism in the world where it normally lives.

pokemon.name: Celesteela
pokemon.pokedex: One of the dangerous UBs,high energy readings can be detected coming from both of its huge arms.

pokemon.name: Kartana
pokemon.pokedex: This Ultra Beast's body,which is as thin as paper,is like a sharpened sword.

pokemon.name: Guzzlord
pokemon.pokedex: Although it's alien to this world and a danger here,it's apparently a common organism in the world where it normally lives.

pokemon.name: Necrozma
pokemon.pokedex: It looks somehow pained as it rages around in search of light,which serves as its energy. It's apparently from another world.

pokemon.name: Magearna
pokemon.pokedex: It synchronizes its consciousness with others to understand their feelings. This faculty makes it useful for taking care of people.

pokemon.name: Marshadow
pokemon.pokedex: It slips into the shadows of others and mimics their powers and movements. As it improves,it becomes stronger than those it's imitating.

pokemon.name: Poipole
pokemon.pokedex: This Ultra Beast is well enough liked to be chosen as a first partner in its own world.

pokemon.name: Naganadel
pokemon.pokedex: It stores hundreds of liters of poisonous liquid inside its body. It is one of the organisms known as UBs.

pokemon.name: Stakataka
pokemon.pokedex: It appeared from an Ultra Wormhole. Each one appears to be made up of many life-forms stacked one on top of each other.

pokemon.name: Blacephalon
pokemon.pokedex: It slithers toward people. Then,without warning,it triggers the explosion of its own head. It's apparently one kind of Ultra Beast.

pokemon.name: Zeraora
pokemon.pokedex: It electrifies its claws and tears its opponents apart with them. Even if they dodge its attack,they'll be electrocuted by the flying sparks.

pokemon.name: Meltan
pokemon.pokedex: It melts particles of iron and other metals found in the subsoil,so it can absorb them into its body of molten steel.

pokemon.name: Melmetal
pokemon.pokedex: Revered long ago for its capacity to create iron from nothing,for some reason it has come back to life after 3,000 years.

pokemon.name: Grookey
pokemon.pokedex: It attacks with rapid jolts of its stick. As it strikes with amazing speed,it gets more and more charged.

pokemon.name: Thwackey
pokemon.pokedex: When it's drumming out rapid beats in battle,it gets so caught up in the rhythm that it won't even notice that it's already knocked out its opponent.

pokemon.name: Rillaboom
pokemon.pokedex: Its ferocious drumming summons violent thunderstorms. It uses wind currents to direct its electric attacks.

pokemon.name: Scorbunny
pokemon.pokedex: It has special pads on the backs of its feet,and one on its nose. Once it's raring to fight,these pads radiate tremendous heat.

pokemon.name: Raboot
pokemon.pokedex: It kicks berries right off the branches of trees and then juggles them with its feet,practicing its footwork.

pokemon.name: Cinderace
pokemon.pokedex: It's skilled at both offense and defense,and it gets pumped up when cheered on. But if it starts showboating,it could put itself in a tough spot.

pokemon.name: Sobble
pokemon.pokedex: When it gets wet,its skin changes color,and this Pokemon becomes invisible as if it were camouflaged.

pokemon.name: Drizzile
pokemon.pokedex: Highly intelligent but also very lazy,it keeps enemies out of its territory by laying traps everywhere.

pokemon.name: Inteleon
pokemon.pokedex: Its nictitating membranes let it pick out foes' weak points so it can precisely blast them with water that shoots from its fingertips at Mach 3.

pokemon.name: Skwovet
pokemon.pokedex: It eats berries nonstop,a habit that has made it more resilient than it looks. It'll show up on farms,searching for yet more berries.

pokemon.name: Greedent
pokemon.pokedex: Common throughout the Galar region,this Pokémon has strong teeth and can chew through the toughest of berry shells.

pokemon.name: Rookidee
pokemon.pokedex: Jumping nimbly about,this small-bodied Pokémon takes advantage of even the slightest opportunity to disorient larger opponents.

pokemon.name: Corvisquire
pokemon.pokedex: The lessons of many harsh battles have taught it how to accurately judge an opponent's strength.

pokemon.name: Corviknight
pokemon.pokedex: With their great intellect and flying skills,these Pokémon very successfully act as the Galar region's airborne taxi service.

pokemon.name: Blipbug
pokemon.pokedex: Often found in gardens,this Pokémon has hairs on its body that it uses to assess its surroundings.

pokemon.name: Dottler
pokemon.pokedex: As it grows inside its shell,it uses its psychic abilities to monitor the outside world and prepare for evolution.

pokemon.name: Orbeetle
pokemon.pokedex: It emits psychic energy to observe and study what's around it,and what's around it can include things over six miles away.

pokemon.name: Nickit
pokemon.pokedex: They will create clouds under their paws and use them to float,blending in with the sky. They will often float up to mountains and steal eggs from bird Pokemon's nests.

pokemon.name: Thievul
pokemon.pokedex: Creating clouds under its paws,it races through the skies- swooping down below if it spots something shiny.

pokemon.name: Gossifleur
pokemon.pokedex: It whirls around in the wind while singing a joyous song. This delightful display has charmed many into raising this Pokémon.

pokemon.name: Eldegoss
pokemon.pokedex: The cotton on the head of this Pokémon can be spun into a glossy,gorgeous yarn,a Galar regional specialty.

pokemon.name: Wooloo
pokemon.pokedex: If its fleece grows too long,Wooloo won't be able to move. Cloth made with the wool of this Pokémon is surprisingly strong.

pokemon.name: Dubwool
pokemon.pokedex: Its majestic horns are meant only to impress the opposite gender. They never see use in battle.

pokemon.name: Chewtle
pokemon.pokedex: It starts off battles by attacking with its rock-hard horn,but as soon as the opponent flinches,this Pokémon bites down and never lets go.

pokemon.name: Drednaw
pokemon.pokedex: This Pokémon rapidly extends its retractable neck to sink its sharp fangs into distant enemies and take them down.

pokemon.name: Yamper
pokemon.pokedex: This gluttonous Pokémon only assists people with their work because it wants treats. As it runs,it crackles with electricity.

pokemon.name: Boltund
pokemon.pokedex: It sends electricity through its legs to boost their strength. Running at top speed,it easily breaks 50 mph.

pokemon.name: Rolycoly
pokemon.pokedex: It can race around like a unicycle,even on rough,rocky terrain. Burning coal sustains it.

pokemon.name: Carkol
pokemon.pokedex: By rapidly rolling its legs,it can travel at over 18 mph. The temperature of the flames it breathes exceeds 1,800 degrees Fahrenheit.

pokemon.name: Coalossal
pokemon.pokedex: While it's engaged in battle,its mountain of coal will burn bright red,sending off sparks that scorch the surrounding area.

pokemon.name: Applin
pokemon.pokedex: As soon as it's born,it burrows into an apple. Not only does the apple serve as its food source,but the flavor of the fruit determines its evolution.

pokemon.name: Flapple
pokemon.pokedex: It flies on wings of apple skin and spits a powerful acid. It can also change its shape into that of an apple.

pokemon.name: Appletun
pokemon.pokedex: Its body is covered in sweet nectar,and the skin on its back is especially yummy. Children used to have it as a snack.

pokemon.name: Silicobra
pokemon.pokedex: It spews sand from its nostrils. While the enemy is blinded,it burrows into the ground to hide.

pokemon.name: Sandaconda
pokemon.pokedex: Its unique style of coiling allows it to blast sand out of its sand sac more efficiently.

pokemon.name: Cramorant
pokemon.pokedex: This hungry Pokémon swallows Arrokuda whole. Occasionally,it makes a mistake and tries to swallow a Pokémon other than its preferred prey.

pokemon.name: Arrokuda
pokemon.pokedex: After it's eaten its fill,its movements become extremely sluggish. That's when Cramorant swallows it up.

pokemon.name: Barraskewda
pokemon.pokedex: It spins its tail fins to propel itself,surging forward at speeds of over 100 knots before ramming prey and spearing into them.

pokemon.name: Toxel
pokemon.pokedex: It manipulates the chemical makeup of its poison to produce electricity. The voltage is weak,but it can cause a tingling paralysis.

pokemon.name: Toxtricity
pokemon.pokedex: This short-tempered and aggressive Pokémon chugs stagnant water to absorb any toxins it might contain.

pokemon.name: Sizzlipede
pokemon.pokedex: Its tiny metal shell floats around its central core. Its inexperience with its gravity powers keeps it erratically afloat.

pokemon.name: Centiskorch
pokemon.pokedex: Its segmented metal body provides incredible protection and flexibility giving it. Centiskorch has a unique power to manipulate gravity,allowing it to alter its weight and create localized gravitational fields.

pokemon.name: Clobbopus
pokemon.pokedex: Its tentacles tear off easily,but it isn't alarmed when that happens,it knows they'll grow back. It's about as smart as a three-year-old.

pokemon.name: Grapploct
pokemon.pokedex: Searching for an opponent to test its skills against,it emerges onto land. Once the battle is over,it returns to the sea.

pokemon.name: Sinistea
pokemon.pokedex: The teacup in which this Pokémon makes its home is a famous piece of antique tableware. Many forgeries are in circulation.

pokemon.name: Polteageist
pokemon.pokedex: Leaving leftover black tea unattended is asking for this Pokémon to come along and pour itself into it,turning the tea into a new Polteageist.

pokemon.name: Hatenna
pokemon.pokedex: Aware of its cuteness,it invites itself in the dens of other Pokemon and slowly fills them with spider webs.

pokemon.name: Hattrem
pokemon.pokedex: Its leg-hairs have enough power to bend a metal pole in two. Because of this,they have no natural predators,and thrive in gloomy forests.

pokemon.name: Hatterene
pokemon.pokedex: It plays with its prey with unimaginable cruelty. Usually,it leaves the poor victim's life hanging on by a thread,literally.

pokemon.name: Impidimp
pokemon.pokedex: It sneaks into people's homes,stealing things and feasting on the negative energy of the frustrated occupants.

pokemon.name: Morgrem
pokemon.pokedex: With sly cunning,it tries to lure people into the woods. Some believe it to have the power to make crops grow.

pokemon.name: Grimmsnarl
pokemon.pokedex: Its hairs work like muscle fibers. When its hairs unfurl,they latch on to opponents,ensnaring them as tentacles would.

pokemon.name: Twirlaroon
pokemon.pokedex: It evolved after experiencing numerous fights. While crossing its arms,it lets out a shout that would make any opponent flinch.

pokemon.name: Perrserker
pokemon.pokedex: After many battles,it evolved dangerous claws that come together to form daggers when extended.

pokemon.name: Cursola
pokemon.pokedex: Be cautious of the ectoplasmic body surrounding its soul. You'll become stiff as stone if you touch it.

pokemon.name: Sirfetch'd
pokemon.pokedex: After deflecting attacks with its hard leaf shield,it strikes back with its sharp leek stalk. The leek stalk is both weapon and food.

pokemon.name: Mr. Rime
pokemon.pokedex: Its amusing movements make it very popular. It releases its psychic power from the pattern on its belly.

pokemon.name: Runerigus
pokemon.pokedex: Never touch its shadowlike body,or you'll be shown the horrific memories behind the picture carved into it.

pokemon.name: Milcery
pokemon.pokedex: They say that any patisserie visited by Milcery is guaranteed success and good fortune.

pokemon.name: Alcremie
pokemon.pokedex: A run-in with a mixer caused the cream to spiral. Those lucky enough to taste its rich flavour say it's to die for.

pokemon.name: Falinks
pokemon.pokedex: The six of them work together as one Pokémon. Teamwork is also their battle strategy,and they constantly change their formation as they fight.

pokemon.name: Pincurchin
pokemon.pokedex: It stores electricity in each spine. Even if one gets broken off,it still continues to emit electricity for at least three hours.

pokemon.name: Snom
pokemon.pokedex: It eats snow that piles up on the ground. The more snow it eats,the bigger and more impressive the spikes on its back grow.

pokemon.name: Frosmoth
pokemon.pokedex: It shows no mercy to any who desecrate fields and mountains. It will fly around on its icy wings,causing a blizzard to chase offenders away.

pokemon.name: Stonjourner
pokemon.pokedex: Once a year,on a specific date and at a specific time,they gather out of nowhere and form up in a circle.

pokemon.name: Eiscue
pokemon.pokedex: This Pokémon keeps its heat-sensitive head cool with ice. It fishes for its food,dangling its single hair into the sea to lure in prey.

pokemon.name: Indeedee
pokemon.pokedex: Through its horns,it can pick up on the emotions of creatures around it. Positive emotions are the source of its strength.

pokemon.name: Morpeko
pokemon.pokedex: It carries electrically roasted seeds with it as if they're precious treasures. No matter how much it eats,it always gets hungry again in short order.

pokemon.name: Cufant
pokemon.pokedex: If a job requires serious strength,this Pokémon will excel at it. Its copper body tarnishes in the rain,turning a vibrant green color.

pokemon.name: Copperajah
pokemon.pokedex: These Pokémon live in herds. Their trunks have incredible grip strength,strong enough to crush giant rocks into powder.

pokemon.name: Dracozolt
pokemon.pokedex: The powerful muscles in its tail generate its electricity. Compared to its lower body,its upper half is entirely too small.

pokemon.name: Arctozolt
pokemon.pokedex: This Pokémon lived on prehistoric seashores and was able to preserve food with the ice on its body. It went extinct because it moved so slowly.

pokemon.name: Dracovish
pokemon.pokedex: Its mighty legs are capable of running at speeds exceeding 40 mph,but this Pokémon can't breathe unless it's underwater.

pokemon.name: Arctovish
pokemon.pokedex: The skin on its face is impervious to attack,but breathing difficulties made this Pokémon go extinct anyway.

pokemon.name: Duraludon
pokemon.pokedex: The special metal that composes its body is very light,so this Pokémon has considerable agility. It lives in caves because it dislikes the rain.

pokemon.name: Dreepy
pokemon.pokedex: If this weak Pokémon is by itself,a mere child could defeat it. But if Dreepy has friends to help it train,it can evolve and become much stronger.

pokemon.name: Drakloak
pokemon.pokedex: Without a Dreepy to place on its head and care for,it gets so uneasy it'll try to substitute any Pokémon it finds for the missing Dreepy.

pokemon.name: Dragapult
pokemon.pokedex: Apparently the Dreepy inside Dragapult's horns eagerly look forward to being launched out at Mach speeds.

pokemon.name: Zacian
pokemon.pokedex: This Pokémon has slumbered for many years. Some say it's Zamazenta's elder sister,others say the two Pokémon are rivals.

pokemon.name: Zamazenta
pokemon.pokedex: This Pokémon slept for aeons while in the form of a statue. It was asleep for so long,people forgot that it ever existed.

pokemon.name: Eternatus
pokemon.pokedex: It was inside a meteorite that fell 20,000 years ago. There seems to be a connection between this Pokémon and the Dynamax phenomenon.

pokemon.name: Kubfu
pokemon.pokedex: If Kubfu pulls the long white hair on its head,its fighting spirit heightens and power wells up from the depths of its belly.

pokemon.name: Urshifu
pokemon.pokedex: Inhabiting the mountains of a distant region,this Pokémon races across sheer cliffs,training its legs and refining its moves.

pokemon.name: Zarude
pokemon.pokedex: Once the vines on Zarude's body tear off,they become nutrients in the soil. This helps the plants of the forest grow.

pokemon.name: Regieleki
pokemon.pokedex: Its entire body is made up of an single organ that generates electrical energy. Regieleki is capable of creating all of Galar's electricity.

pokemon.name: Regidrago
pokemon.pokedex: Its body is composed of crystalized dragon energy. Regidrago is said to have the powers of every dragon Pokemon.

pokemon.name: Glastrier
pokemon.pokedex: Glastrier has tremendous physical strength,and the mask of ice covering its face is 100 times harder than diamond.

pokemon.name: Spectrier
pokemon.pokedex: As it dashes through the night,Spectrier absorbs the life-force of sleeping creatures. It craves silence and solitude.

pokemon.name: Cyndaquil
pokemon.pokedex: It flares flames from its back to protect itself. The fire burns vigorously if the Pokémon is angry. When it is tired,it sputters with incomplete combustion.

pokemon.name: Quilava
pokemon.pokedex: When it dashes through the night,one can see a trail of spirits following close behind it.

pokemon.name: Typhlosion
pokemon.pokedex: The spirits of the dead are attracted to Typhlosion. Their unrelentless ferocity have gained them the nickname "The White Wraiths".

pokemon.name: Chikorita
pokemon.pokedex: Said to have gone extinct shortly after the war,a few specimen have been found in the natural caves of Citrine Jungle.

pokemon.name: Bayleef
pokemon.pokedex: The many buds decorating this Pokemon's neck are a fashion icon in a faraway region. Records found after the war imply that this Pokemon may have originated from that land.

pokemon.name: Meganium
pokemon.pokedex: These incredibly rare Pokemon form natural shrines in the secluded jungles they live in,adorning them with the pink leaves of their tail.

pokemon.name: Totodile
pokemon.pokedex: Its powerful,well-developed jaws are capable of crushing anything. Even its Trainer must be careful.

pokemon.name: Croconaw
pokemon.pokedex: Once it bites down,it won't let go until it loses its fangs. New fangs quickly grow into place.

pokemon.name: Feraligatr
pokemon.pokedex: This Pokemon lives to fight,and it doesn't hold personal grudges. There's been multiple sightings of this Pokemon and Gyarados wrestling it out at sea.

pokemon.name: Shroomish
pokemon.pokedex: It spouts poison spores from the top of its head. These spores cause pain all over if inhaled.

pokemon.name: Breloom
pokemon.pokedex: It scatters poisonous spores and throws powerful punches while its foe is hampered by inhaled spores.

pokemon.name: Hoothoot
pokemon.pokedex: Friendlier and more intelligent compared to its Johtonian counterpart. It waves to humans and other Pokemon,hoping to study their reaction.

pokemon.name: Noctowl
pokemon.pokedex: Ayreian Noctowl use their heightened intelligence and ability to fly silently through the night to expertly hunt their prey.

pokemon.name: Ferroseed
pokemon.pokedex: It absorbs the iron it finds in the rock while clinging to the ceiling. It shoots spikes when in danger.

pokemon.name: Ferrothorn
pokemon.pokedex: They attach themselves to cave ceilings,firing steel spikes at targets passing beneath them.

pokemon.name: Geodude
pokemon.pokedex: Said to be spirits of hikers that have perished in the various mountains of Ayrei. They control their limbs independently from the main body.

pokemon.name: Graveler
pokemon.pokedex: It burrows deep in caves,indistinguishable from nearby rocks. Graveler can rest for days like this,hidden from people and Pokemon alike.

pokemon.name: Golem
pokemon.pokedex: Caves haunted by this Pokemon are off-limits to even the most experienced of trainers. Its spectral limbs carry it with incredible speed,surprising most.

pokemon.name: Butterfree
pokemon.pokedex: It uses its enhanced brainpower to sense predators from up to 50 miles away.

pokemon.name: Swablu
pokemon.pokedex: While cute and seemingly docile,it angers really quickly. They nest in areas most often hit by thunderstorms.

pokemon.name: Altaria
pokemon.pokedex: Only seen during thunderstorms,they brave the dark skies uncontested in both ferocity and boldness.

pokemon.name: Snorlax
pokemon.pokedex: For some reason,this Pokemon believes it is the king of the mountain,yet the only thing it does all day is sleep.

pokemon.name: Growlithe
pokemon.pokedex: The spirit of a loyal Pokemon has reanimated itself with a guardian statue as its vessel. It searches restlessly for something.

pokemon.name: Arcanine
pokemon.pokedex: Ayreian Arcanines have a fierce sense of loyalty,and will willingly destroy their vessel to ensure their loved ones safety.

pokemon.name: Mareep
pokemon.pokedex: It's fur is extremely rough,enough to even leave cuts on your hand if rubbed the wrong way.

pokemon.name: Flaaffy
pokemon.pokedex: Being made of metals,its nearly indestructable horns can also absorb electrity.

pokemon.name: Ampharos
pokemon.pokedex: Thanks to it's strong legs and small wings,Ampharos can jump long distances and even stay in the air for a few seconds.

pokemon.name: Weedle
pokemon.pokedex: It wriggles around slowly,seemingly defenseless,before striking opponents it's own size that get too close,pulling them into the ground.

pokemon.name: Kakuna
pokemon.pokedex: While awaiting evolution,it hides from predators underground.

pokemon.name: Beedrill
pokemon.pokedex: If faced with a stronger opponent,it dives underground before reappearing from below.

pokemon.name: Shinx
pokemon.pokedex: All of its fur dazzles if danger is sensed. It flees while the foe is momentarily blinded.

pokemon.name: Luxio
pokemon.pokedex: Strong electricity courses through the tips of its sharp claws. A light scratch causes fainting in foes.

pokemon.name: Luxray
pokemon.pokedex: When in danger,the pattern on its forehead shines brightly. Its retractable claws are overcharged with high voltage electricity.

pokemon.name: Magnemite
pokemon.pokedex: At times,Magnemite runs out of fuel and ends up on the ground. If you give coal to a grounded Magnemite,it'll start moving again.

pokemon.name: Magneton
pokemon.pokedex: The two heads that aren't constantly burning are always trying to detatch themselves from the third head,with little result.

pokemon.name: Magnemelt
pokemon.pokedex: It is so surrounded by magma that you'll almost never see it's original body.

pokemon.name: Merlicun
pokemon.pokedex: It isn't considered very useful in any way what so ever. It seems to just want to crawl around and eat leaves.

pokemon.name: Firomenis
pokemon.pokedex: Firomenis use the lights from their tails combined with their extreme speed to scare away predators.

pokemon.name: Pancham
pokemon.pokedex: It does its level best to glare and pull a scary face,but it can't help grinning if anyone pats its head.

pokemon.name: Enchantowl
pokemon.pokedex: When it needs to think,it rotates its head 180 degrees to sharpen its intellectual power.

pokemon.name: Timburr
pokemon.pokedex: Timburr seem to love the idea of building homes out of wood,but lose their mind at the sight of steel.

pokemon.name: Gurdurr
pokemon.pokedex: It carries around a giant log for hours upon hours without rest.

pokemon.name: Conkeldurr
pokemon.pokedex: Concrete mixed by Conkeldurr is much more durable than normal concrete,even when the compositions of the two materials are the same.

pokemon.name: Wolfum
pokemon.pokedex: It collects the fallen hairs and sheddings of other Pokemon to build a wolflike body,allowing it to blend in with other Pokemon.

pokemon.name: Supiritto
pokemon.pokedex: This Pokémon will pretend to be an empty shedding and wait for it's prey to get close enough before attacking.

pokemon.name: Amacorala
pokemon.pokedex: It stores high amounts of water inside of its body,which it then shoots as precise water jets.

pokemon.name: Solacor
pokemon.pokedex: The highly pressurized water inside of its body burst during evolution. It can slide to quickly evade attacks,and shoot pressurized water jets.

pokemon.name: Dunmyth
pokemon.pokedex: It digs into the ground with its tail and makes a mazelike nest. It can fly just a little.

pokemon.name: Dundragon
pokemon.pokedex: It can't fly,but it will use it's wings to jump incredibly high and reach enemies.

pokemon.name: Loathedisc
pokemon.pokedex: It spreads endless dread throughout the seas it swims.

pokemon.name: Panvolt
pokemon.pokedex: It's good at finding berries and gathers them from all over. It's kind enough to share them with friends.

pokemon.name: Iron Vortex
pokemon.pokedex: This Pokemon does not appear to be of this world. It has a latent power to remove souls from the bodies of the living. A folktale describes a Pokemon like this tracking down and killing a malicious king.
